 (1970) (arranged from the song by Edward MacDowell) (published posthumously)\n*Old MacDonald Had a Farm\n*[[Seventy-Six Trombones]]\n\n;Musical Theater compositions\n*My Sister Eileen (1952) (the music is lost)\n* '''[[Goldilocks (musical)]]''' (1958)\n*# Overture (1958)\n*# Bad Companions (1958)\n*# Come to Me (1958)\n*# Give the Little Lady (1958)\n*# Guess Who (1958)\n*# Heart of Stone (Pyramid Dance) (1958)\n*# He'll Never Stray (1958)\n*# Hello (1958)\n*# I Can't Be in Love (1958)\n*# I Never Know When to Say When (1958)\n*# If I Can't Take it With Me (1958)\n*# Lady in Waiting (1958)\n*# Lazy Moon (1958)\n*# Little Girls (1958)\n*# My Last Spring (1958)\n*# No One Will Ever Love You (1958)\n*# Save a Kiss (1958)\n*# Shall I Take My Heart and Go? (1958)\n*# Tag-a-long Kid (1958)\n*# The Beast in You (1958)\n*# The Pussy Foot (1958)\n*# There Never Was a Woman (1958)\n*# Town House Maxixe (1958)\n*# Two Years in the Making (1958)\n*# Who's Been Sitting in My Chair? (1958)\n* Gone With the Wind (1961)\n*# I'm Too Young to Be a Widow\n*# Fiddle-Dee-Dee\n*# This Lovely World\n\n;Vocal compositions\n*Do You Think That Love Is Here to Stay? (1935)\n*Love May Come and Love May Go (1935)\n*The Music in My Heart (1935)\n*You Can Always Tell a Harvard Man (1962)\n*What's the Use of Love? (1935)\n\n;Organ compositions\n*Cambridge Centennial March of Industry (1946)\n*Easter Song (194-)\n*Wedding March for Jane and Peter (1972)\n\n;Other compositions\n*Hens and Chickens (1966) (for beginning piano)\n*Chatterbox (1966) (for beginning piano)\n*Melody on Two Notes (~1965) (for beginning orchestra)\n*An Old Fashioned Song (196-) (for beginning piano)\n*Piece for Rolf (1961) (for two cellos)\n*The Cowboy and His Horse (1966) (for beginning piano)\n*The Whistling Kettle (~1965) (for beginning orchestra)\n*Woodbury Fanfare (1959) (for four trumpets)\n<ref>\"Leroy Anderson: A Bio-Bibliography\", Praeger 2004, Chapter 2 \u2013 \"Works\", Pages 25\u201381.</ref>\n<ref>\"Published Music\" of the Leroy Anderson's website, maintained by his family.</ref>\n\n==Discography==\nThe following is a selected discography of original recordings by Leroy Anderson. They were released from 1958 to 1962 on 33{{frac|1|3}} rpm discs and on digitally remastered compact discs released posthumously. 78 rpm and 45 rpm discs from 1945 to 1962, and releases of identical recordings on different labels in U.K., Germany, New Zealand and elsewhere, are not listed.<ref>Leroy Anderson: A Bio-Bibliography; Burgess Speed, Eleanor Anderson, Steve Metcalf. \"Discography \u2013 Recordings by the Composer\", Praeger, Westport CT USA; 2004, pp 84\u201394</ref>\n;Recordings by Leroy Anderson\n* ''Leroy Anderson's Irish Suite'' (Decca DL 4050; 1952)\n* ''Christmas Carols'' (Decca DL-8193; 1955)\n* ''Leroy Anderson conducts Blue Tango and Other Favorites'' (Decca DL 8121; 1958)\n* ''A Christmas Festival'' (Decca DL 78925 (s); 1959)\n* ''Leroy Anderson Conducts Leroy Anderson'' (Decca DL 78865 (s); 1959)\n* ''Leroy Anderson Conducts His Music'' (Decca DL 78954 (s); 1960)\n* ''The New Music of Leroy Anderson'' (Decca DL 74335 (s); 1962)\n* ''The Leroy Anderson Collection'' (Digitally remastered from original Decca analog recordings) (MCA Classics MCAD2-9815-A & B; 1988)\n* ''The Best of Leroy Anderson: Sleigh Ride'' (Digitally remastered from original Decca analog master recordings) (MCA Classics MCAD \u221211710; 1997)\n\n==Honors and awards==\n* Phi Beta Kappa, elected June 17, 1929.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/>\n* Music Director, Harvard University Band 1929, 1931\u20131935<ref>Spalding, Walter Raymond: Music at Harvard, New York: Coward-McCann, 1935</ref>\n* Gold Record, ''Blue Tango'', 1952\n* Member, Board of Directors, ASCAP, New York, New York 1960\u20131964\n* Member, Music Department Committee, Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts 1962\u20131968\n* Goldman Citation, American Bandmasters Association, March 10, 1966\n* Phi Mu Alpha Sinfonia, Gamma Omega Chapter (honorary member), Indiana State University, 1969\n* Member of Board of Directors of symphony orchestras:\n** New Haven, Connecticut 1969\u20131975\n** Hartford, Connecticut 1971\u20131975\n* Honorary Doctorate (Ph.D), Portia Law School, Boston, Massachusetts June 1971\n* Honorary Doctorate (Ph.D), Western New England College, Springfield, Massachusetts May 1974\n* Star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]], 1976<ref>{{cite web |url=http://projects.latimes.com/hollywood/star-walk/leroy-anderson/ |title=Leroy Anderson \u2013 Hollywood Star Walk \u2013 Los Angeles Times |publisher=Projects.latimes.com |date=1975-05-19 |access-date=2015-08-17}}</ref>\n* Named to [[Songwriters Hall of Fame]], April 18, 1988<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.songwritershalloffame.org/exhibits/C203 |title=Leroy Anderson Exhibit Home |publisher=Songwriters Hall of Fame |date=1908-06-29 |access-date=2015-08-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150219064338/http://www.songwritershalloffame.org/exhibits/C203 |archive-date=2015-02-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Anderson Band Center, Cambridge, Massachusetts, Harvard University, dedicated October 26, 1995<ref>[http://www.parabrisas.com/d_andersonl.php ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108045142/http://www.parabrisas.com/d_andersonl.php |date=January 8, 2012}}</ref>\n* Leroy Anderson Square, Cambridge, Massachusetts, dedicated May 31, 2003<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://news.harvard.edu/gazette/2003/07.17/12-anderson.html |title=Harvard Gazette: Leroy Anderson Square dedicated |publisher=News.harvard.edu |date=2003-07-17 |access-date=2015-08-17}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n;English\n;;Books\n* Burgess Speed, Eleanor Anderson, Steve Metcalf: ''Leroy Anderson: A Bio-Bibliography'' (Praeger, 2004) {{ISBN|0-313-32176-0}}\n* Howard Pollack, ''Harvard Composers \u2013 Walter Piston and his Students'' (The Scarecrow Press, 1992) {{ISBN|0-8108-2493-0}}\n* Edward Jablonski, ''The Encyclopedia of American Music'' (Doubleday & Co., Inc. 1981) {{ISBN|0-385-08088-3}}\n* George McCue, ''Music in American Society 1776\u20131976'' (Transaction Books., 1977) {{ISBN|978-0-87855-634-2}}\n* Christopher Pavlakis, ''The American Music Handbook'' (MacMillan Publishing Co., Inc., 1974) {{ISBN|0-385-08088-3}}\n* David Ewen, ''Popular American Composers \u2013 from Revolutionary Times to the Present'' (H.W. Wilson Co., 1962)\n* Jan-Erik Ander & Jeremy Lamb (translator): ''New Sweden 1638\u20131988'' (Swedish National Committee for New Sweden '88, 1992) {{ISBN|91-7176-146-2}}\n* Steven Ledbetter: ''100 Years of the Boston Pops'' (Boston Symphony Orchestra, Inc., 1985)\n\n;;Periodicals\n* Joseph Smith: ''Leroy Anderson \u2013 Scandinavian Review'' (American-Scandinavian Foundation, 2009)\n* Eliot Spalding: ''Vita: Leroy Anderson'' (Harvard Review, 1993)\n* Janet Frank: ''Syncopated Clock, Indeed!'' (The American Scholar \u2013 Phi Beta Kappa Society, 2008)\n* Jane Anderson Vercelli: ''Composer Leroy Anderson: Cambridge Born and Bred'' (The Newetowne Chronicle \u2013 Cambridge Historical Society, 2008)\n* Joanne Kaufmann: ''Leroy Anderson: Tuneful Blade Runner'' (Wall Street Journal, 1995)\n* Anthony Tommasini: ''Tuneful Gems from a Master: Leroy Anderson'' (New York Times, 1996)\n* Frederick Fennell: ''Music by Leroy Anderson'' (The Instrumentalist, 1990)\n* Anders Neumueller, editor: ''Leroy Anderson'' (Swedish Press Society, 1994)\n* Andrew & Martha Sherman, editors: ''Annual Report dedication to Leroy Anderson'' (Town of Woodbury, 2008)\n\n;Swedish\n* Svea: ''Svensk\u00e4ttling Ber\u00f6md Amerikansk Komposit\u00f6r''; Worcester, Massachusetts USA; (Svea Publishing Company, weekly Swedish American newspaper, November 10, 1949)\n* Norra Str\u00f6 Hembygdsf\u00f6rening: ''Norra Str\u00f6: Bygden och Folket'' (Norra Str\u00f6 Hembygdsf\u00f6rening, 2009) '' \u2013 documentation of Leroy Anderson's parents birthplaces in Sweden''\n* Carin Dohlman: ''Leroy Andersons Julmusik''; Wellesley, Massachusetts USA; (Gult och Blatt i Boston-New England, 2009)\n\n;German\n* Hans-Walter Berg: ''Leroy Anderson: ein Meister der Miniatur''; Buchloe, Germany; (Neue Blasmusik, 1992)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.leroyanderson.com/}}\n* [http://www.leroyandersonfoundation.org Leroy Anderson Foundation]\n* [http://www.americanmusicpreservation.com/anniversaries.htm#leroyanderson Leroy Anderson Centennial Tribute]\n* [https://www.pbs.org/sleighride Once Upon a Sleigh Ride]&nbsp;\u2014 PBS Web site devoted to a 1999 documentary about Anderson; biographical sketches, photographs, etc.\n* [http://drs.library.yale.edu:8083/saxon/SaxonServlet?style=http://drs.library.yale.edu:8083/saxon/EAD/yul.ead2002.xhtml.xsl&source=http://drs.library.yale.edu:8083/fedora/get/music:mss.0068/EAD&query=achron&filter=&hitPageStart=1 Leroy Anderson Papers at Yale University Music Library]\n*[https://www.namm.org/library/oral-history/eleanor-anderson Eleanor Anderson]&nbsp;\u2014 NAMM Oral History Interview (2007)\n*[https://www.namm.org/library/oral-history/kurt-anderson Kurt Anderson]&nbsp;\u2014 NAMM Oral History Interview (2007)\n\n{{Billboard Year-End number one singles 1946\u20131959}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anderson, Leroy}}\n[[Category:1908 births]]\n[[Category:1975 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American composers]]\n[[Category:20th-century classical composers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male musicians]]\n[[Category:American classical composers]]\n[[Category:American classical musicians]]\n[[Category:American male classical composers]]\n[[Category:American music arrangers]]\n[[Category:American people of Swedish descent]]\n[[Category:Classical musicians from Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Decca Records artists]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Easy listening musicians]]\n[[Category:Harvard College alumni]]\n[[Category:Light music composers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Cambridge, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:People from Woodbury, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Pupils of Walter Piston]]\n[[Category:Writers from Cambridge, Massachusetts]]\n", "name_user": "Rolf.Anderson", "label": "safe", "comment": "Correct ref link to Songwriters Hall of Fame profile of Leroy Anderson", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leroy_Anderson"}
{"title_page": "Eostrix", "text_new": "{{short description|Genus of extinct primitive owls in the family Protostrigidae}}\n{{Italic title}}\n{{Automatic Taxobox\n| name = ''Eostrix''\n| image = \n| fossil_range = early Eocene\n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Eostrix\n| authority = Brodkorb, 1971\n| subdivision_ranks = Species\n| subdivision = \n''E. mimica'' <small>(Wetmore, 1938)</small><br/>\n''E. martinellii'' <small>Martin & Black, 1972</small><br/>\n''E. vincenti'' <small>Harrison 1980</small><br/>\n''E. tsaganica'' <small>Kurochkin& Dyke 2011</small><br/>\n''E. gulottai'' <small>Mayr 2016</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Eostrix''''' is a genus of extinct primitive [[owl]]s in the family [[Protostrigidae]], along with ''Oligostrix'' and ''Minerva''.<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=P_TB72RBLLMC&pg=PA164&dq=Eostrix&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjIpaGn1p3lAhWETd8KHaAKDFsQ6AEwAHoECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=Eostrix&f=false</ref> These owls date from early [[Eocene]] of the [[United States]], [[Europe]], and [[Mongolia]]. They have been described from fossil remains. The genus was created by [[Pierce Brodkorb]] in 1971 to place a fossil species known until that time as ''Protostrix mimica''.\n\nThe following species are recognised:\n* ''E. mimica'' described in 1938 by [[Alexander Wetmore]] using hindlimb elements in Eocene strata in Wyoming.<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=P_TB72RBLLMC&pg=PA164&dq=Eostrix&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjIpaGn1p3lAhWETd8KHaAKDFsQ6AEwAHoECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=Eostrix&f=false</ref>\n* ''E. martinellii'' was described in 1972 from a left [[tarsometatarsus]] (lower leg bone) recovered from an escarpment above the southeastern bank of Cottonwood Creek in [[Fremont County, Wyoming]] by Jorge Martinelli on a field trip in 1970 under the auspices of the University of Kansas. The strata was a Lysite member of the Wind River Formation. Martinelli was studying paleontology at the University of Barcelona. Paleontologists Larry D. Martin and [[Craig Call Black]] from the [[University of Kansas Natural History Museum]] named it in his honour. The smaller of the two species, it was similar in size to the living [[long-eared owl]] (''Asio otus''). Differences in the [[Tarsometatarsus|trochleas]] (grooves) of the lower end of the tarsometatarsus set it apart from living owls, namely a groove in the trochlea for digit 2, a deeper posterior groove in a relatively narrow trochlea for digit 3, and an unusually rounded trochlea for digit 4.<ref name=martinblack>{{cite journal|year=1972|title=A new owl from the Eocene of Wyoming|journal=Auk|volume=89|issue=4|pages=887\u201388|url=http://sora.unm.edu/sites/default/files/journals/auk/v089n04/p0887-p0888.pdf|accessdate=3 November 2010|doi=10.2307/4084122|last1=Martin|first1=Larry D.|last2=Black|first2=Craig C.}}</ref>\n* ''E. vincenti'' described in 1980 by [[Colin Harrison (ornithologist)|Colin Harrison]] from the early Eocene [[London Clay]] in England, known from [[Phalanx bone|pedal phalanx]] and proximal [[tarsometatarsus]] bones.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Harrison|first1=C. J. O. |title=A small owl from the Lower Eocene of Britain|journal=Tertiary Research |volume=3|issue=2|date= 1980|pages= 83-87|issn=0308-9649}}</ref> Some scholars think  ''E. vincenti'' resembles ''[[Necrobyas]]'' more than ''Eostrix''.<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=P_TB72RBLLMC&pg=PA164&dq=Eostrix&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjIpaGn1p3lAhWETd8KHaAKDFsQ6AEwAHoECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=Eostrix&f=false</ref> \n* ''E. tsaganica'' described in 2011 by [[Evgeny Kurochkin]] and [[Gareth J. Dyke]], found in Mongolia.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kurochkin |first1=E. N. |last2=Dyke |first2=G. J. |title=The first fossil owls (Aves: Strigiformes) from the Paleogene of Asia and a review of the fossil record of Strigiformes |journal=Paleontological Journal |date=2011 |volume=45 |issue=4 |pages=445\u2013458 |doi=10.1134/S003103011104006X}}</ref>\n* ''E. gulottai'' described in 2016 by [[Gerald Mayr]], found in the early Eocene [[Nanjemoy Formation]] in [[Virginia]] alongside a dozen other species of birds. This species is the smallest known fossil (or living) owl, with a distal width of 3.9 mm. The structure of its trochlea metatarsi II, a bone in the owl's foot, strongly indicates that it would have restricted the rotation of the second toe. Since a similar bone structure has been observed on birds with webbed feet, this detail has led to the conclusion that the ''E. gulottai'' also had webbed feet. Named for the finder of the [[holotype]], [[Marco Gulotta]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Mayr |first1=Gerald |title=The world\u2019s smallest owl, the earliest unambiguous charadriiform bird, and other avian remains from the early Eocene Nanjemoy Formation of Virginia (USA) |journal=PalZ |date=2016 |volume=90 |issue=4 |pages=747\u2013763 |doi=10.1007/s12542-016-0330-8|url=http://phatfossils.com/pics/Eostrix%20gulottai/Eostrix%20gulottai.pdf}}</ref>\n\n==References==<!-- AmMusNovit2773:1. Auk89:887,99:576. Palaeontology37:339. -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*Mayr, G. ''Paleogene Fossil Birds''. Springer, 2009. p.&nbsp;164.\n\n{{Portal|Paleontology}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5381954}}\n\n[[Category:Eocene birds of North America]]\n[[Category:Protostrigidae]]\n[[Category:Eocene birds of Europe]]\n[[Category:Eocene animals of Asia]]\n\n\n{{paleo-bird-stub}}\n{{Strigiformes-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Genus of extinct primitive owls in the family Protostrigidae}}\n{{Italic title}}\n{{Automatic Taxobox\n| name = ''Eostrix''\n| image = \n| fossil_range = early Eocene\n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Eostrix\n| authority = Brodkorb, 1971\n| subdivision_ranks = Species\n| subdivision = \n''E. mimica'' <small>(Wetmore, 1938)</small><br/>\n''E. martinellii'' <small>Martin & Black, 1972</small><br/>\n''E. vincenti'' <small>Harrison 1980</small><br/>\n''E. tsaganica'' <small>Kurochkin& Dyke 2011</small><br/>\n''E. gulottai'' <small>Mayr 2016</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Eostrix''''' is a genus of extinct primitive [[owl]]s in the family [[Protostrigidae]], along with ''Oligostrix'' and ''Minerva''.<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=P_TB72RBLLMC&pg=PA164&dq=Eostrix&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjIpaGn1p3lAhWETd8KHaAKDFsQ6AEwAHoECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=Eostrix&f=false</ref> These owls date from early [[Eocene]] of the [[United States]], [[Europe]], and [[Mongolia]]. They have been described from fossil remains. The genus was created by [[Pierce Brodkorb]] in 1971 to place a fossil species known until that time as ''Protostrix mimica''.\n\nThe following species are recognised:\n* ''E. mimica'' described in 1938 by [[Alexander Wetmore]] using hindlimb elements in Eocene strata in Wyoming.<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=P_TB72RBLLMC&pg=PA164&dq=Eostrix&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjIpaGn1p3lAhWETd8KHaAKDFsQ6AEwAHoECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=Eostrix&f=false</ref>\n* ''E. martinellii'' was described in 1972 from a left [[tarsometatarsus]] (lower leg bone) recovered from an escarpment above the southeastern bank of Cottonwood Creek in [[Fremont County, Wyoming]] by Jorge Martinelli on a field trip in 1970 under the auspices of the University of Kansas. The strata was a Lysite member of the Wind River Formation. Martinelli was studying paleontology at the University of Barcelona. Paleontologists Larry D. Martin and [[Craig Call Black]] from the [[University of Kansas Natural History Museum]] named it in his honour. The smaller of the two species, it was similar in size to the living [[long-eared owl]] (''Asio otus''). Differences in the [[Tarsometatarsus|trochleas]] (grooves) of the lower end of the tarsometatarsus set it apart from living owls, namely a groove in the trochlea for digit 2, a deeper posterior groove in a relatively narrow trochlea for digit 3, and an unusually rounded trochlea for digit 4.<ref name=martinblack>{{cite journal|year=1972|title=A new owl from the Eocene of Wyoming|journal=Auk|volume=89|issue=4|pages=887\u201388|url=http://sora.unm.edu/sites/default/files/journals/auk/v089n04/p0887-p0888.pdf|accessdate=3 November 2010|doi=10.2307/4084122|last1=Martin|first1=Larry D.|last2=Black|first2=Craig C.}}</ref>\n* ''E. vincenti'' described in 1980 by [[Colin Harrison (ornithologist)|Colin Harrison]] from the early Eocene [[London Clay]] in England, known from [[Phalanx bone|pedal phalanx]] and proximal [[tarsometatarsus]] bones.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Harrison|first1=C. J. O. |title=A small owl from the Lower Eocene of Britain|journal=Tertiary Research |volume=3|date= 1980|pages= 83-87|issn=0308-9649}}</ref> Some scholars think  ''E. vincenti'' resembles ''[[Necrobyas]]'' more than ''Eostrix''.<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=P_TB72RBLLMC&pg=PA164&dq=Eostrix&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjIpaGn1p3lAhWETd8KHaAKDFsQ6AEwAHoECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=Eostrix&f=false</ref> \n* ''E. tsaganica'' described in 2011 by [[Evgeny Kurochkin]] and [[Gareth J. Dyke]], found in Mongolia.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kurochkin |first1=E. N. |last2=Dyke |first2=G. J. |title=The first fossil owls (Aves: Strigiformes) from the Paleogene of Asia and a review of the fossil record of Strigiformes |journal=Paleontological Journal |date=2011 |volume=45 |issue=4 |pages=445\u2013458 |doi=10.1134/S003103011104006X}}</ref>\n* ''E. gulottai'' described in 2016 by [[Gerald Mayr]], found in the early Eocene [[Nanjemoy Formation]] in [[Virginia]] alongside a dozen other species of birds. This species is the smallest known fossil (or living) owl, with a distal width of 3.9 mm. The structure of its trochlea metatarsi II, a bone in the owl's foot, strongly indicates that it would have restricted the rotation of the second toe. Since a similar bone structure has been observed on birds with webbed feet, this detail has led to the conclusion that the ''E. gulottai'' also had webbed feet. Named for the finder of the [[holotype]], [[Marco Gulotta]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Mayr |first1=Gerald |title=The world\u2019s smallest owl, the earliest unambiguous charadriiform bird, and other avian remains from the early Eocene Nanjemoy Formation of Virginia (USA) |journal=PalZ |date=2016 |volume=90 |issue=4 |pages=747\u2013763 |doi=10.1007/s12542-016-0330-8|url=http://phatfossils.com/pics/Eostrix%20gulottai/Eostrix%20gulottai.pdf}}</ref>\n\n==References==<!-- AmMusNovit2773:1. Auk89:887,99:576. Palaeontology37:339. -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*Mayr, G. ''Paleogene Fossil Birds''. Springer, 2009. p.&nbsp;164.\n\n{{Portal|Paleontology}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5381954}}\n\n[[Category:Eocene birds of North America]]\n[[Category:Protostrigidae]]\n[[Category:Eocene birds of Europe]]\n[[Category:Eocene animals of Asia]]\n\n\n{{paleo-bird-stub}}\n{{Strigiformes-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bobamnertiopsis", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:iss", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eostrix"}
{"title_page": "S\u00e9rgio Moro", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian federal judge}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} \n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name              = S\u00e9rgio Moro \n|image             = Medalha da Ordem do Ipiranga ao Ministro S\u00e9rgio Moro - 48146010211 (cropped).jpg\n|office            = [[Ministry of Justice and Public Security (Brazil)|Minister of Justice and Public Security]]\n|term_start        = 1 January 2019\n|term_end          = 24 April 2020\n|president         = [[Jair Bolsonaro]]\n|predecessor       = [[Torquato Jardim]] {{small|(Justice)}}<br />[[Raul Jungmann]] {{small|(Public Security)}}\n|successor         = Position vacant\n|birth_name        = S\u00e9rgio Fernando Moro<ref>{{cite web | url=https://news.nd.edu/news/brazilian-judge-sergio-moro-receives-notre-dame-award/ | title=Brazilian Judge S\u00e9rgio Moro receives Notre Dame Award | first=Dennis | last=Brown | publisher=University of Notre Dame | date=2 October 2017 | accessdate=8 April 2018 }}</ref>\n|birth_date        = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1972|8|01}} \n|birth_place       = [[Maring\u00e1]], [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]], [[Brazil]]\n|education         = [[State University of Maring\u00e1]] {{small|([[Bachelor of Laws|BA]])}}<br />[[Federal University of Paran\u00e1]] {{small|([[Master of Laws|MA]])}} {{small|([[Doctor of Law|PhD]])}}\n|spouse            = Ros\u00e2ngela Wolff de Quadros\n|children          = 2\n|mother            = Odete Starke Moro\n|father            = Dalton \u00c1ureo Moro\n|signature         = Dr Moro do Brazil.png\n}}\n'''S\u00e9rgio Fernando Moro''' ({{IPA-pt|\u02c8s\u025b\u0281\u0292ju \u02c8mo\u027eu|br}}; born 1 August 1972) is a Brazilian [[jurist]], former [[federal judge]] and [[Professor|college professor]] who served as [[Ministry of Justice and Public Security (Brazil)|Minister of Justice and Public Security]] for the government of president [[Jair Bolsonaro]], from 2019 to 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gauchazh.clicrbs.com.br/geral/noticia/2016/04/a-historia-de-sergio-moro-o-juiz-que-sacudiu-o-brasil-com-a-lava-jato-5784184.html|title=A hist\u00f3ria de Sergio Moro, o juiz que sacudiu o Brasil com a Lava-Jato|work=Ga\u00fachaZH|access-date=2018-11-16|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> In 2015 he gained fame in [[Operation Car Wash]] ({{lang-pt|Opera\u00e7\u00e3o Lava Jato}}), a high-profile scandal of corruption and bribery involving government officials and business executives.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/09/business/international/effects-of-petrobras-scandal-leave-brazilians-lamenting-a-lost-dream.html?_r=0 |title=Effects of Petrobras scandal leave Brazilians lamenting a lost dream |date=9 August 2015 |website=The New York Times |url-access=limited |access-date=15 July 2017 |quote=\"If any good has come from the Petrobras debacle it is the flickering sense that this time could be different. Part of the reason is the work of Judge S\u00e9rgio Moro, who is overseeing the investigation, officially known as Opera\u00e7\u00e3o Lava Jato, or Operation Carwash.\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Fernanda|last=Cruz|url=http://agenciabrasil.ebc.com.br/en/politica/noticia/2015-08/sergio-moro-fighting-corruption-should-bring-benefits-brazil|title=Sergio Moro fighting corruption should bring benefits to Brazil|date=31 August 2015|website=[[Ag\u00eancia Brasil]] |access-date=15 July 2017}}\"Federal Judge S\u00e9rgio Moro, in charge of the proceedings opened under Operation Car Wash\"...\"The judge reported that the evidence gathered during the operation as well as the allegations given under plea bargain indicate that the payment of bribes through contracts at Petrobras was a common practice.\"</ref>\n\nOn 29 October 2018, days after the [[2018 Brazilian general election|2018 election]], President-elect [[Jair Bolsonaro]] nominated Moro to be [[Ministry of Justice (Brazil)|Minister of Justice and Public Security]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/politica/2018-10-29/bolsonaro-convidar-juiz-sergio-moro.htmll|title=Bolsonaro vai convidar o ju\u00edz S\u00e9rgio Moro para ser ministro|publisher=\u00daltimo Segundo|language=pt|date=29 October 2018|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> On 1 November, Moro accepted the job after personally meeting with Bolsonaro.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2018/11/01/moro-aceita-convite-de-bolsonaro-para-comandar-o-ministerio-da-justica.ghtml|title=Moro aceita convite de Bolsonaro para comandar o Minist\u00e9rio da Justi\u00e7a|publisher=G1|language=pt|date=1 November 2018|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/nov/01/bolsonaro-sergio-moro-brazil-justice-ministry-anti-corruption|title=Bolsonaro appoints judge who helped jail Lula to lead justice ministry|publisher=The Guardian|language=en|date=1 November 2018|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> His appointment to Bolsonaro's cabinet and the way he had previously conducted Operation Car Wash (in particular [[Luiz In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva|President Lula]]'s case) drew praise from his peers and by a significant portion of the Brazilian society, but also significant criticism was voiced, especially after revelations of alleged partiality and [[judicial misconduct]] on his part, published by the American investigative journalist [[Glenn Greenwald]], during the Car Wash investigations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/glenn-greenwald-has-faced-pushback-for-his-reporting-before-but-not-like-this/2019/07/11/9a7f3590-a1b1-11e9-bd56-eac6bb02d01d_story.html|title=Glenn Greenwald has faced pushback for his reporting before. But not like this.|last=McCoy|first=Terrence|date=July 13, 2019|work=The Washington Post|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/jul/16/brazil-glenn-greenwald-investigation-bolsonaro|title=Brazil must reveal investigations into journalist Glenn Greenwald, court says|last=Press|first=Associated|date=2019-07-16|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://riotimesonline.com/brazil-news/rio-politics/national-politics/federal-police-plans-false-flag-arrest-and-confession-of-vaza-jato-leaks-hacker-says-intercept/|title=Federal Police Plan Arrest and Fake Confession of Vaza Jato Hacker, Says Intercept|last=Petrov|first=Arkady|date=2019-07-16|website=The Rio Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/20/world/americas/brazil-bolsonaro-greenwald.html|title=\u2018The Antithesis of Bolsonaro\u2019: A Gay Couple Roils Brazil\u2019s Far Right|last=Londo\u00f1o|first=Ernesto|date=2019-07-20|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/bresil-tentative-de-piratage-des-telephones-de-bolsonaro-20190725|title=Br\u00e9sil: tentative de piratage des t\u00e9l\u00e9phones de Bolsonaro|date=2019-07-25|website=FIGARO|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/the-brazilian-justice-ministers-dubious-deportation-decree/a-49816025|title=The Brazilian justice minister's dubious deportation decree {{!}} DW {{!}} 30.07.2019|last=Welle (www.dw.com)|first=Deutsche|website=DW.COM|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref> Moro left the government in April 2020, mentioning the President's undue interferences in the affairs of the Ministry of Justice.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/04/24/moro-anuncia-demissao-do-ministerio-da-justica-e-deixa-o-governo-bolsonaro.ghtml |title=Ex-juiz Sergio Moro anuncia demiss\u00e3o do Minist\u00e9rio da Justi\u00e7a e deixa o governo Bolsonaro |language=Portuguese |trans-title=Former judge Sergio Moro announces resignation of the Ministry of Justice and leaves the Bolsonaro's government |work =G1.com |access-date= 24 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nMoro was born in [[Maring\u00e1]],<ref name=\"joice hasselmann\">{{cite book |last=Hasselmann |first= Joice |year=2016 |title=S\u00e9rgio Moro: a Hist\u00f3ria do Homem por Tr\u00e1s da Opera\u00e7\u00e3o que Mudou o Brasil |trans-title=S\u00e9rgio Moro: The History of the Man Behind the Operation that Changed Brazil |url= |location=S\u00e3o Paulo |publisher=Universo dos Livros |pages=208 |isbn=8550300217 |language=pt-br}}</ref> son of Odete Starke Moro and Dalton \u00c1ureo Moro, a former professor of [[geography]] at the [[State University of Maring\u00e1]], who died in 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.oguaira.com.br/sergio-moro-o-queridinho-do-brasil/ |title= S\u00e9rgio Moro \u2013 o queridinho do Brasil |work = O Gua\u00edra |date= 19 March 2016 |access-date= 9 April 2016}}</ref> His elder sibling, C\u00e9sar Fernando Moro, owns a technology company.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.escavador.com/sobre/2137454/cesar-fernando-moro |title=C\u00e9sar Fernando Moro |work =Escavador |date=3 January 2016 |access-date= 10 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Campo Grande News\">{{cite web |url=http://www.campograndenews.com.br/colunistas/em-pauta/um-juiz-de-vida-espartana-sergio-moro-o-juiz-que-abalou-a-republica |title=Um juiz de vida espartana. S\u00e9rgio Moro, o juiz que abalou a Rep\u00fablica |work =Campo Grande News | first =M\u00e1rio S\u00e9rgio |last = Lorenzetto |date=27 April 2015 |access-date=10 April 2016}}</ref> The Moro family moved to [[Ponta Grossa]] when S\u00e9rgio and C\u00e9sar were children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.recantodasletras.com.br/textosjuridicos/5905194|title=S\u00c9RGIO MORO - O juiz que o Brasil nunca esquecer\u00e1|work=Recanto das Letras|access-date=2018-11-19|language=pt-br}}</ref>{{Better source|date=November 2018}} He is of Italian descent, with origins in the region of [[Veneto]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://oguaira.com.br/editorial/sergio-moro-o-queridinho-do-brasil/ |title=S\u00e9rgio Moro \u2013 o queridinho do Brasil |work = |date=19 March 2016 |access-date= 15 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nMoro is married to Ros\u00e2ngela Wolff de Quadros, a [[lawyer]] and current legal solicitor of the National Association of Parents and Friends of Exceptional Children (''Associa\u00e7\u00e3o de Pais e Amigos dos Excepcionais''). They live in [[Curitiba]] and have a couple of school-age children.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticias.r7.com/brasil/dois-anos-apos-lava-jato-sergio-moro-troca-de-carro-e-passa-a-andar-com-seguranca-24-horas-17032016|title=Dois anos ap\u00f3s Lava Jato, S\u00e9rgio Moro troca de carro e passa a andar com seguran\u00e7a 24 horas|publisher=Record|work=R7|first1=Mariana|last1=Londres|first2=Marc|last2=Sousa|date=17 March 2015|access-date=10 April 2016}}</ref> In addition to his professional career, little is known about his personal life.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publico.pt/mundo/noticia/sergio-moro-o-juiz-de-curitiba-que-tem-o-futuro-do-brasil-nas-maos-1704455|title=S\u00e9rgio Moro, o juiz de Curitiba que tem o futuro do Brasil nas m\u00e3os|work=P\u00fablico|date=9 August 2015|access-date=24 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazetadopovo.com.br/vida-publica/sergio-moro-um-ilustrissimo-desconhecido-de3447fcdify2ue6d0cs2cvuv|title=S\u00e9rgio Moro, um ilustr\u00edssimo desconhecido|work=Gazeta do Povo|first=Rogerio Waldrigues|last=Galindo|date=11 December 2015|access-date=6 March 2016}}</ref> An article published in December 2014 by ''[[Isto\u00e9|Isto\u00c9]]'' magazine described him as someone with \"reserved lifestyle and simple habits\".<ref name=\"Isto \u00c9\" />\n\n=== Academic education ===\nMoro got a [[Law]] degree from [[State University of Maring\u00e1]] in 1995.<ref name=\"Isto \u00c9\">{{Cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/pr/parana/noticia/2018/11/01/sergio-moro-veja-quem-e-o-juiz-que-ganhou-projecao-nacional-com-a-lava-jato.ghtml|title=S\u00e9rgio Moro: veja quem \u00e9 o juiz que ganhou proje\u00e7\u00e3o nacional com a Lava Jato|work=G1|access-date=2018-11-17|language=pt-BR}}</ref> During his studies, he interned in a law firm for two years, being described as a \"sensational person\" by the lawyer who hired him.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=jhABDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA6&lpg=PA6#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=S\u00e9rgio Moro: Guia Conhecer Fant\u00e1stico Atualidades Ed.01|last=Editora|first=On Line|last2=Editora|first2=Pol\u00edtica On Line|date=2016-04-20|publisher=On Line Editora|language=en}}</ref> He attended a summer course at [[Harvard Law School]] in 1998, including studies on money laundering promoted by the [[United States Department of State|US Department of State]].<ref name=\"Isto \u00c9\" /> He received his [[master's degree]] in 2000 from the [[Federal University of Paran\u00e1]] with the dissertation ''\"Development and Judicial Enforcement of Constitutional Norms\"'', guided by Professor [[Cl\u00e8merson Merlin Cl\u00e8ve]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304114304/http://oasisbr.ibict.br/vufind/Record/UFPR_012cb29379cb3d50fa41d776addaf166/Details|title=Staff View: Desenvolvimento e efetiva\u00e7\u00e3o judicial das normas constitucionais|date=2017-03-04|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref><ref>Moro, S\u00e9rgio Fernando. [https://acervodigital.ufpr.br/bitstream/handle/1884/43018/Desenvolvimento%20e%20efetivacao%20judicial%20das%20normas%20constitucionais.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y Development and Judicial Enforcement of Constitutional Norms]. Dissertation presented to the Law Postgraduate Degree of the Federal University of Paran\u00e1, as a partial requirement to obtain the Master's degree, having as advisor Prof. Dr. Cl\u00e8merson Merlin Cl\u00e8ve. Curitiba, 2000.</ref> In 2002, he completed a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] in State Law at the same institution with the thesis ''\"Constitutional Jurisdiction as Democracy\"'', guided by [[Mar\u00e7al Justen Filho]].<ref>Moro, S\u00e9rgio Fernando. [https://acervodigital.ufpr.br/bitstream/handle/1884/43165/Tese%20Moro.pdf?sequence=1 ''Jurisdi\u00e7\u00e3o constitucional como democracia'']. Thesis presented to the Postgraduate Course in Law of the Federal University of Paran\u00e1, as a partial requirement to obtain the title of Doctor, having as advisor Prof. Dr. Mar\u00e7al Justen Filho. Curitiba, 2002.</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://noticias.r7.com/brasil/rapido-discreto-e-obstinado-conheca-o-juiz-que-se-tornou-o-pesadelo-dos-acusados-na-lava-jato-14042015|title=R\u00e1pido, discreto e obstinado: conhe\u00e7a o juiz que se tornou o pesadelo dos acusados na Lava Jato|date=2015-04-14|work=R7.com|access-date=2018-11-19|language=pt-BR}}</ref> In 2007, he participated in the [[International Visitor Leadership Program]] in which he visited U.S. agencies and institutions responsible for preventing and combating money laundering.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://buscatextual.cnpq.br/buscatextual/visualizacv.do?id=K8747305D4#FormacaoAcademicaTitulacao|title=Curriculum vitae|last1=Moro|first1=Sergio|date=28 October 2013|website=Curr\u00edculo Lattes|publisher=CNPq|language=Portuguese|access-date=8 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 1996, Moro started teaching to law graduates at his ''[[alma mater]]'', the [[Federal University of Paran\u00e1]]. This very same year, he became a [[federal judge]] in [[Porto Alegre]], before moving to [[Joinville, Santa Catarina]], in 1999. Between 2003 and 2007, Moro worked in a case involving the public bank Banestado. The investigation resulted in the arrest of nearly 200 people for [[tax evasion]] and [[money laundering]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/pr/parana/noticia/2014/11/comissao-aprova-homenagens-sergio-moro-e-ao-papa-na-assembleia.html|title=Comiss\u00e3o aprova homenagens a S\u00e9rgio Moro e ao Papa na Assembleia|date=25 November 2014|publisher=G1|language=Portuguese|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, he worked with [[Rosa Weber]], a minister of the [[Supreme Federal Court|Brazilian Supreme Court]], in the [[Mensal\u00e3o scandal|''Mensal\u00e3o'' scandal]]. Weber called him because of his experience with cases involving financial crimes, more specifically money laundering.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/poder/51967-grupo-de-juizes-auxilia-stf-no-julgamento-do-mensalao.shtml|title=Grupo de ju\u00edzes auxilia STF no julgamento do mensal\u00e3o|publisher=Folha de S\u00e3o Paulo|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Operation Car Wash ===\n{{Main|Operation Car Wash}}\n[[File:S\u00e9rgio Moro (cropped).jpg|thumb|Moro in 2015.]]\nIn 2014, while working in [[Curitiba]], Sergio Moro became one of the head judges in [[Operation Car Wash]] ({{lang-pt|Opera\u00e7\u00e3o Lava Jato}}), a massive criminal investigation that started as a money laundering case and evolved to a huge corruption scandal crackdown, involving bribery and misappropriation of public funds by political authorities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ebc.com.br/noticias/politica/2016/03/saiba-porque-lava-jato-e-considerada-maior-investigacao-sobre-corrupcao-da|title=Saiba por que a Lava Jato \u00e9 considerada a maior investiga\u00e7\u00e3o da hist\u00f3ria do Brasil|publisher=|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> The investigation was modeled after [[Mani pulite]] in Italy.<ref name=\"mani\">{{cite web | url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2019/08/anti-corruption-crusades-paved-way-bolsonaro/596449/ | title=The Dirty Problems With Operation Car Wash | publisher=The Atlantic | date=21 August 2019 | accessdate=22 August 2019 | author=Bevins, Vincent}}</ref> Corruption scandals in Brazil usually take a long time to investigate and the whole legal process tends to drag. However, at an unusual speed, Moro authorized further investigations, detentions and questioning of suspects.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://politica.estadao.com.br/blogs/fausto-macedo/moro-sonha-com-fim-da-lava-jato-ate-dezembro/|title= Moro sonha com o fim da Lava Jato at\u00e9 dezembro|publisher=Estadao|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> By late 2017, at least 120 sentences were carried and 175 people were sent to jail. Despite some criticism from fellow jurists for being a \"media darling\", Moro enjoyed high popularity with the Brazilian people and became one of the main faces in the fight against corruption in the country, at least in the public eye.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/world-latin-america-35978337/who-is-sergio-moro-the-judge-making-brazil-s-headlines|title=Who is Sergio Moro, the judge making Brazil\u2019s headlines?|publisher=BBC|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nDespite the criticism of the speed with which he passed the sentences for such a huge case,<ref>{{cite web|url= http://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2016/10/04/estamos-em-tempos-excepcionais-diz-moro-ao-defender-prisoes-preventivas.htm|title='Estamos em tempos excepcionais', diz Moro ao defender pris\u00f5es preventivas|publisher=UOL|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> his actions received the backing of the Brazilian Supreme Court and most of his sentences and decisions were upheld in higher courts.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.em.com.br/app/noticia/politica/2016/10/04/interna_politica,810853/em-dois-anos-e-meio-apenas-tres-sentencas-da-lava-jato-chegaram-ao-fi.shtml|title=Em dois anos e meio, apenas tr\u00eas senten\u00e7as da Lava Jato chegaram ao final no TRF4|publisher=|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> By late 2016, Moro had sent 28 people to jail on charges of corruption, with four of them having their sentences reduced by a higher judge and four being set free upon further deliberation. Overall, in Operation Car Wash, 71% of the sentences given by Moro were upheld by the Brazilian [[Regional Federal Courts]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://politica.estadao.com.br/blogs/fausto-macedo/tribunal-ratifica-ou-sobe-pena-de-71-dos-condenados-por-moro/|title=Tribunal ratifica ou sobe pena de 71% dos condenados por Moro|publisher=O Estado de S.\u202fPaulo|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Moro sentenced former Brazilian president, [[Luiz In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva]], to 9 and a half years in jail, on the charges of money laundering and passive corruption. The sentencing caused an uproar in Brazil, with many widely supporting and saluting the judge for his decision, with others claiming he was getting ahead of himself.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/05/world/americas/brazil-lula-prison.html|title=Judge Orders Brazil\u2019s Ex-President \u2018Lula\u2019 to Begin Prison Term on Friday|publisher=The New York Times|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> Lula was considered the frontrunner for the 2018 presidential election.<ref name=\"mani\"/>\n\n=== Minister of Justice ===\nDuring his many encounters with media and further interviews, Sergio Moro always called himself \"apolitical\" and said he had no interested in joining the political world. However, right after the [[2018 Brazilian general election|2018 elections]], rumors started to circulate that the president-elect of Brazil, [[Jair Bolsonaro]], was considering nominating Moro to head the [[Ministry of Justice (Brazil)|Ministry of Justice]]. Despite claiming he was unaware of plans to make him justice minister before his invitation, it was later discovered that Moro was contacted by Paulo Guedes, an incoming member of Bolsonaro's administration, during Bolsonaro\u2019s election campaign.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Albuquerque |first1=Carlos |title=Controversial appointment |url=https://www.dandc.eu/en/article/brazils-newly-appointed-justice-minister-accused-political-interference |website= D+C, development and cooperation}}</ref> Exactly four days after the election, on 1 November 2018, Moro met with Bolsonaro in [[Rio de Janeiro]], and it was then announced that, in fact, he would become a minister in Bolsonaro's administration.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2018/11/01/moro-aceita-convite-de-bolsonaro-para-comandar-o-ministerio-da-justica.ghtml|title=Moro aceita convite de Bolsonaro para comandar o Minist\u00e9rio da Justi\u00e7a|publisher=G1|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-10-18/bolsonaro-embraces-aura-of-anti-graft-judge-in-campaign-push|title=This Man Is Playing a Big Role in Brazil\u2019s Election\u2014and He Isn\u2019t Even on the Ballot|publisher=Bloomberg.com|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nHis nomination was well received by fellow [[magistrate]]s across the country,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/brasil/associacao-dos-magistrados-elogia-a-escolha-de-moro-para-ministerio-01112018|title=Associa\u00e7\u00e3o dos Magistrados elogia a escolha de Moro para Minist\u00e9rio|publisher=R7|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> but opponents of Bolsonaro and some of the press criticized the decision on the grounds of conflict of interest, claiming that Moro's sentencing of former president Lu\u00eds In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva greatly benefited Bolsonaro's bid for the presidency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/internacional/ultimas-noticias/2018/11/01/analise-por-que-a-nomeacao-de-moro-por-bolsonaro-caiu-mal-na-imprensa-internacional.htm|title=An\u00e1lise: Por que a nomea\u00e7\u00e3o de Moro por Bolsonaro caiu mal na imprensa internacional?|publisher=UOL|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 May 2019, president Bolsonaro expressed the intention of nominating Moro to the Supreme Federal Court, replacing Justice [[Celso de Mello]], who will retire, at age 75, in 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2019/05/12/bolsonaro-diz-que-vai-indicar-sergio-moro-para-vaga-no-stf.ghtml|title=Bolsonaro diz que vai indicar S\u00e9rgio Moro para vaga no STF|publisher=G1|language=pt|first=Luiz Felipe|last=Babi\u00e9ri|date=12 May 2019|accessdate=13 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 April 2020, after an unjustified discharge of [[Federal Police of Brazil|Federal Police]]'s Director-General Maur\u00edcio Valeixo by president Bolsonaro, Moro announced he would leave the Ministry, while denouncing the president's intention to meddle in investigations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2020/04/sergio-moro-o-juiz-da-lava-jato-anuncia-sua-demissao-do-governo-bolsonaro.shtml|title=Sergio Moro, o juiz da Lava Jato, anuncia sua demiss\u00e3o do governo Bolsonaro|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|language=pt|first=Leandro|last=Colon|date=24 April 2020|accessdate=24 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\n[[File:Entrevistas Diversas (21094916379).jpg|thumb|right|Moro holding a press conference in September 2015]]\nMoro's methods have been questioned by his peers and audited by Brazilian Justices since 2005.<ref name=\"conjur.com.br\">{{cite web|url=http://www.conjur.com.br/2015-mai-05/excessos-sergio-moro-sao-discutidos-cnj-2005|title=Excessos de Sergio Moro s\u00e3o discutidos no STF e no CNJ pelo menos desde 2005|publisher=}}</ref> In 2007, when a defendant wasn't to be found at home, he issued an order to monitor the lists of passengers of all airliners flying from Ciudad del Este in Paraguay and from Porto Alegre in Brazil to Curitiba in order to track the movements of the defendant's attorneys.<ref name=\"conjur.com.br\"/> From 2007 through 2010, he issued an order to record and collect all phone communications and visitor booth talks between all inmates, their families and attorneys at Catanduvas Federal Penitentiary in order to \"prevent future crimes\".<ref name=\"conjur.com.br\"/>\n\nThese cases, among others, have been considered excesses and have brought grave criticism on Moro. Justice [[Celso de Mello]] has officially accused Moro of condoning a \"nosy police state\" and acting as an \"investigative judge\".<ref name=\"conjur.com.br\"/> Additionally, Brazilian Justice [[Gilmar Mendes]] said he was worried about Moro's actions. For him, the case showed a \"set of abusive acts\" and \"objectionable excesses\" practiced by the judge. In his dissenting opinion he wrote that they are \"unacceptable behaviors in which resistance or nonconformity of the magistrate is envisaged, when contradicted by decision of superior instance\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://politica.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,supremo-ja-analisou-excesso-de-moro-no-caso-banestado,10000023234|title=Supremo j\u00e1 analisou \u2018excesso\u2019 de Moro no caso Banestado - Pol\u00edtica - Estad\u00e3o|work=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=2018-11-19|language=pt-BR}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 December 2016, at a ceremony in which Moro was awarded a Man of the Year prize by Brazilian Editora Tr\u00eas publishing house, Moro was photographed laughing alongside Brazilian Senator [[A\u00e9cio Neves]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2016/12/07/viu-esta-foto-entenda-o-que-esta-por-tras-da-polemica-despertada-por-ela.htm|title=Viu esta foto? Entenda por que a descontra\u00e7\u00e3o entre Moro e A\u00e9cio repercutiu - Not\u00edcias - Pol\u00edtica|publisher=}}</ref> [[PSDB]]'s candidate in Brazil's [[2014 Brazilian general election|2014 Presidential Election]] and main critic of [[Workers' Party (Brazil)|PT]]'s tenures in office. Since PT is the party most scrutinized by Operation Carwash, the photograph has caused an uproar among PT supporters. During an interview, Moro has said that \"the photograph was unfortunate, but there's no bias in my decisions as a judge\", while also remarking that Neves is not under his jurisdiction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2016/12/1840125-moro-diz-que-foto-com-aecio-foi-infeliz-mas-nega-parcialidade.shtml|title=Moro diz que foto com A\u00e9cio foi 'infeliz', mas nega parcialidade|publisher=}}</ref>  Neves was accused by five witnesses at Operation Carwash<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/parlatorio/quem-nao-conhece-o-esquema-do-aecio-sergio-machado|title=\"Quem n\u00e3o conhece o esquema do A\u00e9cio?\", pergunta Sergio Machado|first=Jos\u00e9|last=Antonio|publisher=}}</ref> of taking R$300,000 in bribes from [[Alberto Youssef]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/parlatorio/aecio-neves-teria-recebido-r-300-mil-em-propina-da-utc-diz-delator|title=A\u00e9cio Neves teria recebido R$ 300 mil em propina da UTC, diz delator|first=|last=marcelop|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe speed with which Moro has treated specific actions that involve figures from the Brazilian left and his courteous relationship with members of the former opposition, some of which under investigation themselves, has been criticized by Brazilian jurists<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redebrasilatual.com.br/politica/2018/01/juristas-denunciam-lawfare-no-brasil-atraves-de-carta-internacional|title=Juristas denunciam 'lawfare' no Brasil atrav\u00e9s de carta internacional|publisher=}}</ref> and left-wing activists and politicians, who accuse Moro of being part of a [[lawfare]] strategy<ref>{{cite web|url=http://justificando.cartacapital.com.br/2018/04/10/a-ultraceleridade-seletiva-da-lava-jato-e-forma-de-lawfare/|title=A ultraceleridade seletiva da Lava Jato \u00e9 forma de Lawfare|date=10 April 2018|publisher=}}</ref> in order to ostracize PT and bring PSDB to power.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cartacampinas.com.br/2018/06/x-ocupado-com-pt-e-viagens-internacionais-moro-esta-sem-tempo-para-julgar-corrupcao-do-psdb/|title=Ocupado com PT e viagens internacionais, Moro est\u00e1 sem tempo para julgar corrup\u00e7\u00e3o do PSDB|date=12 June 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nDuring a lecture at Harvard University in 2017, S\u00e9rgio Moro stated that he considers the use of [[slush funds|undeclared donations]] \u2013 a crime in Brazilian electoral law \u2013 to fund elections more damaging than illicit enrichment through corruption: \"If I take this bribe and deposit the money in Switzerland, the money stays there, it isn\u2019t harming anyone at the moment. If, however, I use the money to fraud and win an election, I find that terrible.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://politica.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,caixa-2-e-pior-que-corrupcao-para-enriquecimento-ilicito,70001732141 |title=Caixa 2 \u00e9 pior que corrup\u00e7\u00e3o para enriquecimento il\u00edcito, diz S\u00e9rgio Moro |date=8 April 2017 |website=Estad\u00e3o |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.valor.com.br/politica/4931997/para-moro-caixa-dois-e-pior-que-enriquecimento-ilicito |title=Para Moro, caixa dois \u00e9 pior que enriquecimento il\u00edcito |date=8 April 2017 |website= Valor Econ\u00f4mico |access-date= 8 December 2018}}</ref> On May, 2017, then-congressman [[Onyx Lorenzoni]] admitted to having used slush funds donated by [[JBS S.A.|JBS]] in his 2014 campaign for Congress.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://congressoemfoco.uol.com.br/especial/noticias/em-video-deputado-onyx-lorenzoni-admite-ter-recebido-dinheiro-de-caixa-2/ |title=Onyx Lorenzoni admite ter recebido dinheiro de caixa dois da JBS |date=19 May 2017 |website=Congresso em Foco |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2018/10/braco-direito-de-bolsonaro-admitiu-ter-recebido-em-caixa-2-da-jbs.shtml |title=Bra\u00e7o direito de Bolsonaro admitiu ter recebido caixa 2 da JBS |date=15 October 2018 |website=Folha de S\u00e3o Paulo |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.valor.com.br/politica/5971261/moro-diz-admirar-colega-de-ministerio-que-recebeu-caixa-2-da-jbs |title=Moro diz \"admirar\" colega de minist\u00e9rio que recebeu caixa 2 da JBS |date=6 November 2018 |website=Valor Econ\u00f4mico |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref> Lorenzoni has been appointed [[Chief of Staff of Brazil|Chief of Staff]] by president-elect Jair Bolsonaro;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/eleicoes/2018/noticias/2018/10/30/quem-e-onyx-lorenzoni-ministro-da-casa-civil-do-governo-de-jair-bolsonaro.htm |title=Quem \u00e9 Onyx Lorenzoni, futuro ministro da Casa Civil no governo Bolsonaro |date=30 October 2018 |website=Folha de S\u00e3o Paulo |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref> upon being questioned by the press about Lorenzoni\u2019s public admission on the use of slush funds, Moro has stated that Lorenzoni has already apologized to him and has his \"personal trust\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/moro-lista-propostas-e-diz-que-perseguicao-politica-a-lula-e-alibi-falso/ |title=Em coletiva, Moro explica diverg\u00eancias com Bolsonaro e lista propostas |date=6 November 2018 |website=Exame |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noticias.r7.com/brasil/moro-defende-onyx-lorenzoni-e-diz-que-confia-em-seu-trabalho-04122018 |title=Moro defende Onyx Lorenzoni e diz que confia em seu trabalho |date=4 December 2018 |website=R7 |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2018/11/06/sergio-moro-ministro-governo-bolsonaro-pacote-anticorrupcao-membros-lava-jato.htm |title=Moro aponta Lava Jato e pacote anticorrup\u00e7\u00e3o como nortes e v\u00ea Bolsonaro \"ponderado\" |date=6 November 2018 |website=UOL |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://agenciabrasil.ebc.com.br/politica/noticia/2018-12/moro-reafirma-confianca-pessoal-em-onyx |title=Moro reafirma \"confian\u00e7a pessoal\" em Onyx |date=4 December 2018 |website=Ag\u00eancia Brasil |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://veja.abril.com.br/politica/moro-diz-ter-confianca-pessoal-em-onyx-que-admitiu-caixa-dois/ |title=Moro diz ter \"confian\u00e7a pessoal\" em Onyx, que admitiu caixa dois |date=4 December 2018 |website=Veja |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref> In November, 2018, Senator [[Roberto Requi\u00e3o]] proposed a bill called \"Lorenzoni Law\", which would grant immediate pardon for anyone found guilty of electoral and public administration crimes or crimes against the national financial system, as long as they ask for forgiveness. This proposal, although official, has been considered a joke on Moro\u2019s statements.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2018/11/requiao-ironiza-moro-e-propoe-projeto-de-lei-onyx-lorenzoni.shtml |title=Requi\u00e3o ironiza Moro e prop\u00f5e projeto de lei \"\u00d4nix Lorenzoni\" |date=8 November 2018 |website=Folha de S\u00e3o Paulo |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://politica.estadao.com.br/blogs/coluna-do-estadao/requiao-ironiza-moro-e-propoe-lei-onyx-para-perdoar-arrependidos/ |title=Requi\u00e3o ironiza Moro e prop\u00f5e \u2018Lei Onyx\u2019 para perdoar arrependidos |date=8 November 2018 |website=Estad\u00e3o |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/requiao-cria-projeto-lorenzoni-de-perdao-a-criminosos-arrependidos/ |title=Requi\u00e3o prop\u00f5e \"Lei Lorenzoni\" de perd\u00e3o para criminosos arrependidos |date=8 November 2018 |website=Exame |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Telegram leaks ===\n{{Vaza Jato |expanded=all}}\nOn 9 June 2019, the online newspaper ''[[The Intercept]]'' published leaked [[Telegram (app)|Telegram]] messages between Moro and the Operation Car Wash lead prosecutor [[Deltan Dallagnol]], in which Moro allegedly sent advice and instructions to the prosecutor in order to interfere in the investigation that ultimately led to the trial and imprisonment of former president Lula da Silva.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theintercept.com/2019/06/09/brazil-lula-operation-car-wash-sergio-moro/|title=Breach of Ethics: Exclusive: Leaked Chats Between Brazilian Judge and Prosecutor Who Imprisoned Lula Reveal Prohibited Collaboration and Doubts Over Evidence|last=Fishman|first=Andrew|last2=Martins|first2=Rafael Moro|date=2019-06-09|website=The Intercept|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-10|last3=Demori|first3=Leandro|last4=Santi|first4=Alexandre de|last5=Greenwald|first5=Glenn}}</ref> He was accused of not showing impartiality as a judge of da Silva's trial.<ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/25/world/americas/bolsonaro-brazil-phone-hack-corruption.html|title=Jair Bolsonaro, Brazil President, Says His Phones Were Hacked|author=Londo\u00f1o, Ernesto|date=25 July 2019|publisher=The New York Times|accessdate=1 August 2019}}</ref> Three days later, another conversation was leaked, revealing a secret meeting between Dallagnol and Supreme Court Justice [[Luiz Fux]], asking for his support against the then fellow Supreme Court judge [[Teori Zavascki]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/operacao-lava-jato/noticia/2019/06/12/em-nova-mensagem-divulgada-por-site-dallagnol-diz-que-fux-apoiou-moro-em-queda-de-braco-com-teori.ghtml|title=Em nova mensagem divulgada por site, Dallagnol diz que Fux apoiou Moro em 'queda de bra\u00e7o' com Teori|date=12 June 2019|publisher=G1|language=pt|trans-title=In New Message Published By Website, Dallagnol Says That Fux Supported Moro In 'Arm Wrestling' With Teori|accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref> Moro has thoroughly denied any wrongdoing during the course of Operation Carwash and claimed that the [[Vaza Jato|conversations leaked]] by ''The Intercept'' were misrepresented by the press.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/app/noticia/politica/2019/06/10/interna_politica,761721/nao-tem-orientacao-nenhuma-ali-diz-moro-antes-de-abandonar-coletiva.shtml|title=Moro nega ter orientado procuradores da Lava-Jato e abandona entrevista|date=2019-06-10|website=Correio Braziliense|language=pt-br|access-date=2019-07-01}}</ref> He also claimed that the messages could be inauthentic.<ref name=\"nytimes\" />\n\nOn June 12th, Brazilian news magazine ''[[Veja (magazine)|Veja]]'' published a report accusing Moro of \u201cillegally\u201d steering prosecutors as they worked to convict Brazilian politicians and \"overstepping his role as judge,\" claiming that its journalists had spent a fortnight pouring over nearly 650,000 leaked messages between officials involved in the investigation, and concluded the former judge was guilty of serious \u201cirregularities.\u201d Following the report, Moro released a statement condemning \u201cthe distorted and sensationalist diffusion of supposed messages obtained by criminal means.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://veja.abril.com.br/politica/dialogos-veja-capa-intercept-moro-dallagnol/|title=Novos di\u00e1logos revelam que Moro orientava ilegalmente a\u00e7\u00f5es da Lava Jato|website=VEJA.com|language=pt-BR|access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/jul/05/brazil-sergio-moro-jair-bolsonaro-justice-minister|title=Brazil: calls grow for Bolsonaro ally to quit after 'devastating' report on leaks|last=correspondent|first=Tom Phillips Latin America|date=2019-07-05|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-09-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Torquato Jardim]]<br />{{small|''as Minister of Justice''}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Ministry of Justice and Public Security (Brazil)|Minister of Justice and Public Security]]|rows=2|years=2019\u20132020}}\n{{s-vac|rows=2}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Raul Jungmann]]<br />{{small|''as Minister of Public Security''}}}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Bolsonaro cabinet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moro, Sergio}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Maring\u00e1]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Venetian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian judges]]\n[[Category:Brazilian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Ministers of Justice of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Federal University of Paran\u00e1 faculty]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Brazilian federal judge}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} \n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name              = S\u00e9rgio Moro \n|image             = Medalha da Ordem do Ipiranga ao Ministro S\u00e9rgio Moro - 48146010211 (cropped).jpg\n|office            = [[Ministry of Justice and Public Security (Brazil)|Minister of Justice and Public Security]]\n|term_start        = 1 January 2019\n|term_end          = 24 April 2020\n|president         = [[Jair Bolsonaro]]\n|predecessor       = [[Torquato Jardim]] {{small|(Justice)}}<br />[[Raul Jungmann]] {{small|(Public Security)}}\n|successor         = Position vacant\n|birth_name        = S\u00e9rgio Fernando Moro<ref>{{cite web | url=https://news.nd.edu/news/brazilian-judge-sergio-moro-receives-notre-dame-award/ | title=Brazilian Judge S\u00e9rgio Moro receives Notre Dame Award | first=Dennis | last=Brown | publisher=University of Notre Dame | date=2 October 2017 | accessdate=8 April 2018 }}</ref>\n|birth_date        = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1972|8|01}} \n|birth_place       = [[Maring\u00e1]], [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]], [[Brazil]]\n|education         = [[State University of Maring\u00e1]] {{small|([[Bachelor of Laws|BA]])}}<br />[[Federal University of Paran\u00e1]] {{small|([[Master of Laws|MA]])}} {{small|([[Doctor of Law|PhD]])}}\n|spouse            = Ros\u00e2ngela Wolff de Quadros\n|children          = 2\n|mother            = Odete Starke Moro\n|father            = Dalton \u00c1ureo Moro\n|signature         = Dr Moro do Brazil.png\n}}\n'''S\u00e9rgio Fernando Moro''' ({{IPA-pt|\u02c8s\u025b\u0281\u0292ju \u02c8mo\u027eu|br}}; born 1 August 1972) is a Brazilian [[jurist]], former [[federal judge]] and [[Professor|college professor]] who served as [[Ministry of Justice and Public Security (Brazil)|Minister of Justice and Public Security]] for the government of president [[Jair Bolsonaro]], from 2019 to 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gauchazh.clicrbs.com.br/geral/noticia/2016/04/a-historia-de-sergio-moro-o-juiz-que-sacudiu-o-brasil-com-a-lava-jato-5784184.html|title=A hist\u00f3ria de Sergio Moro, o juiz que sacudiu o Brasil com a Lava-Jato|work=Ga\u00fachaZH|access-date=2018-11-16|language=pt-BR}}</ref> In 2015 he gained fame in [[Operation Car Wash]] ({{lang-pt|Opera\u00e7\u00e3o Lava Jato}}), a high-profile scandal of corruption and bribery involving government officials and business executives.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/09/business/international/effects-of-petrobras-scandal-leave-brazilians-lamenting-a-lost-dream.html?_r=0 |title=Effects of Petrobras scandal leave Brazilians lamenting a lost dream |date=9 August 2015 |website=The New York Times |url-access=limited |access-date=15 July 2017 |quote=\"If any good has come from the Petrobras debacle it is the flickering sense that this time could be different. Part of the reason is the work of Judge S\u00e9rgio Moro, who is overseeing the investigation, officially known as Opera\u00e7\u00e3o Lava Jato, or Operation Carwash.\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Fernanda|last=Cruz|url=http://agenciabrasil.ebc.com.br/en/politica/noticia/2015-08/sergio-moro-fighting-corruption-should-bring-benefits-brazil|title=Sergio Moro fighting corruption should bring benefits to Brazil|date=31 August 2015|website=[[Ag\u00eancia Brasil]] |access-date=15 July 2017}}\"Federal Judge S\u00e9rgio Moro, in charge of the proceedings opened under Operation Car Wash\"...\"The judge reported that the evidence gathered during the operation as well as the allegations given under plea bargain indicate that the payment of bribes through contracts at Petrobras was a common practice.\"</ref>\n\nOn 29 October 2018, days after the [[2018 Brazilian general election|2018 election]], President-elect [[Jair Bolsonaro]] nominated Moro to be [[Ministry of Justice (Brazil)|Minister of Justice and Public Security]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/politica/2018-10-29/bolsonaro-convidar-juiz-sergio-moro.htmll|title=Bolsonaro vai convidar o ju\u00edz S\u00e9rgio Moro para ser ministro|publisher=\u00daltimo Segundo|language=pt|date=29 October 2018|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> On 1 November, Moro accepted the job after personally meeting with Bolsonaro.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2018/11/01/moro-aceita-convite-de-bolsonaro-para-comandar-o-ministerio-da-justica.ghtml|title=Moro aceita convite de Bolsonaro para comandar o Minist\u00e9rio da Justi\u00e7a|publisher=G1|language=pt|date=1 November 2018|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/nov/01/bolsonaro-sergio-moro-brazil-justice-ministry-anti-corruption|title=Bolsonaro appoints judge who helped jail Lula to lead justice ministry|publisher=The Guardian|language=en|date=1 November 2018|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> His appointment to Bolsonaro's cabinet and the way he had previously conducted Operation Car Wash (in particular [[Luiz In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva|President Lula]]'s case) drew praise from his peers and by a significant portion of the Brazilian society, but also significant criticism was voiced, especially after revelations of alleged partiality and [[judicial misconduct]] on his part, published by the American investigative journalist [[Glenn Greenwald]], during the Car Wash investigations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/glenn-greenwald-has-faced-pushback-for-his-reporting-before-but-not-like-this/2019/07/11/9a7f3590-a1b1-11e9-bd56-eac6bb02d01d_story.html|title=Glenn Greenwald has faced pushback for his reporting before. But not like this.|last=McCoy|first=Terrence|date=July 13, 2019|work=The Washington Post|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/jul/16/brazil-glenn-greenwald-investigation-bolsonaro|title=Brazil must reveal investigations into journalist Glenn Greenwald, court says|last=Press|first=Associated|date=2019-07-16|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://riotimesonline.com/brazil-news/rio-politics/national-politics/federal-police-plans-false-flag-arrest-and-confession-of-vaza-jato-leaks-hacker-says-intercept/|title=Federal Police Plan Arrest and Fake Confession of Vaza Jato Hacker, Says Intercept|last=Petrov|first=Arkady|date=2019-07-16|website=The Rio Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/20/world/americas/brazil-bolsonaro-greenwald.html|title=\u2018The Antithesis of Bolsonaro\u2019: A Gay Couple Roils Brazil\u2019s Far Right|last=Londo\u00f1o|first=Ernesto|date=2019-07-20|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/bresil-tentative-de-piratage-des-telephones-de-bolsonaro-20190725|title=Br\u00e9sil: tentative de piratage des t\u00e9l\u00e9phones de Bolsonaro|date=2019-07-25|website=FIGARO|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/the-brazilian-justice-ministers-dubious-deportation-decree/a-49816025|title=The Brazilian justice minister's dubious deportation decree {{!}} DW {{!}} 30.07.2019|last=Welle (www.dw.com)|first=Deutsche|website=DW.COM|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref> Moro left the government in April 2020, mentioning the President's undue interferences in the affairs of the Ministry of Justice.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/04/24/moro-anuncia-demissao-do-ministerio-da-justica-e-deixa-o-governo-bolsonaro.ghtml |title=Ex-juiz Sergio Moro anuncia demiss\u00e3o do Minist\u00e9rio da Justi\u00e7a e deixa o governo Bolsonaro |language=Portuguese |trans-title=Former judge Sergio Moro announces resignation of the Ministry of Justice and leaves the Bolsonaro's government |work =G1.com |access-date= 24 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nMoro was born in [[Maring\u00e1]],<ref name=\"joice hasselmann\">{{cite book |last=Hasselmann |first= Joice |year=2016 |title=S\u00e9rgio Moro: a Hist\u00f3ria do Homem por Tr\u00e1s da Opera\u00e7\u00e3o que Mudou o Brasil |trans-title=S\u00e9rgio Moro: The History of the Man Behind the Operation that Changed Brazil |url= |location=S\u00e3o Paulo |publisher=Universo dos Livros |pages=208 |isbn=8550300217 |language=pt-br}}</ref> son of Odete Starke Moro and Dalton \u00c1ureo Moro, a former professor of [[geography]] at the [[State University of Maring\u00e1]], who died in 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.oguaira.com.br/sergio-moro-o-queridinho-do-brasil/ |title= S\u00e9rgio Moro \u2013 o queridinho do Brasil |work = O Gua\u00edra |date= 19 March 2016 |access-date= 9 April 2016}}</ref> His elder sibling, C\u00e9sar Fernando Moro, owns a technology company.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.escavador.com/sobre/2137454/cesar-fernando-moro |title=C\u00e9sar Fernando Moro |work =Escavador |date=3 January 2016 |access-date= 10 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Campo Grande News\">{{cite web |url=http://www.campograndenews.com.br/colunistas/em-pauta/um-juiz-de-vida-espartana-sergio-moro-o-juiz-que-abalou-a-republica |title=Um juiz de vida espartana. S\u00e9rgio Moro, o juiz que abalou a Rep\u00fablica |work =Campo Grande News | first =M\u00e1rio S\u00e9rgio |last = Lorenzetto |date=27 April 2015 |access-date=10 April 2016}}</ref> The Moro family moved to [[Ponta Grossa]] when S\u00e9rgio and C\u00e9sar were children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.recantodasletras.com.br/textosjuridicos/5905194|title=S\u00c9RGIO MORO - O juiz que o Brasil nunca esquecer\u00e1|work=Recanto das Letras|access-date=2018-11-19|language=pt-br}}</ref>{{Better source|date=November 2018}} He is of Italian descent, with origins in the region of [[Veneto]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://oguaira.com.br/editorial/sergio-moro-o-queridinho-do-brasil/ |title=S\u00e9rgio Moro \u2013 o queridinho do Brasil |work = |date=19 March 2016 |access-date= 15 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nMoro is married to Ros\u00e2ngela Wolff de Quadros, a [[lawyer]] and current legal solicitor of the National Association of Parents and Friends of Exceptional Children (''Associa\u00e7\u00e3o de Pais e Amigos dos Excepcionais''). They live in [[Curitiba]] and have a couple of school-age children.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticias.r7.com/brasil/dois-anos-apos-lava-jato-sergio-moro-troca-de-carro-e-passa-a-andar-com-seguranca-24-horas-17032016|title=Dois anos ap\u00f3s Lava Jato, S\u00e9rgio Moro troca de carro e passa a andar com seguran\u00e7a 24 horas|publisher=Record|work=R7|first1=Mariana|last1=Londres|first2=Marc|last2=Sousa|date=17 March 2015|access-date=10 April 2016}}</ref> In addition to his professional career, little is known about his personal life.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publico.pt/mundo/noticia/sergio-moro-o-juiz-de-curitiba-que-tem-o-futuro-do-brasil-nas-maos-1704455|title=S\u00e9rgio Moro, o juiz de Curitiba que tem o futuro do Brasil nas m\u00e3os|work=P\u00fablico|date=9 August 2015|access-date=24 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazetadopovo.com.br/vida-publica/sergio-moro-um-ilustrissimo-desconhecido-de3447fcdify2ue6d0cs2cvuv|title=S\u00e9rgio Moro, um ilustr\u00edssimo desconhecido|work=Gazeta do Povo|first=Rogerio Waldrigues|last=Galindo|date=11 December 2015|access-date=6 March 2016}}</ref> An article published in December 2014 by ''[[Isto\u00e9|Isto\u00c9]]'' magazine described him as someone with \"reserved lifestyle and simple habits\".<ref name=\"Isto \u00c9\" />\n\n=== Academic education ===\nMoro got a [[Law]] degree from [[State University of Maring\u00e1]] in 1995.<ref name=\"Isto \u00c9\">{{Cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/pr/parana/noticia/2018/11/01/sergio-moro-veja-quem-e-o-juiz-que-ganhou-projecao-nacional-com-a-lava-jato.ghtml|title=S\u00e9rgio Moro: veja quem \u00e9 o juiz que ganhou proje\u00e7\u00e3o nacional com a Lava Jato|work=G1|access-date=2018-11-17|language=pt-BR}}</ref> During his studies, he interned in a law firm for two years, being described as a \"sensational person\" by the lawyer who hired him.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=jhABDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA6&lpg=PA6#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=S\u00e9rgio Moro: Guia Conhecer Fant\u00e1stico Atualidades Ed.01|last=Editora|first=On Line|last2=Editora|first2=Pol\u00edtica On Line|date=2016-04-20|publisher=On Line Editora|language=en}}</ref> He attended a summer course at [[Harvard Law School]] in 1998, including studies on money laundering promoted by the [[United States Department of State|US Department of State]].<ref name=\"Isto \u00c9\" /> He received his [[master's degree]] in 2000 from the [[Federal University of Paran\u00e1]] with the dissertation ''\"Development and Judicial Enforcement of Constitutional Norms\"'', guided by Professor [[Cl\u00e8merson Merlin Cl\u00e8ve]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304114304/http://oasisbr.ibict.br/vufind/Record/UFPR_012cb29379cb3d50fa41d776addaf166/Details|title=Staff View: Desenvolvimento e efetiva\u00e7\u00e3o judicial das normas constitucionais|date=2017-03-04|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref><ref>Moro, S\u00e9rgio Fernando. [https://acervodigital.ufpr.br/bitstream/handle/1884/43018/Desenvolvimento%20e%20efetivacao%20judicial%20das%20normas%20constitucionais.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y Development and Judicial Enforcement of Constitutional Norms]. Dissertation presented to the Law Postgraduate Degree of the Federal University of Paran\u00e1, as a partial requirement to obtain the Master's degree, having as advisor Prof. Dr. Cl\u00e8merson Merlin Cl\u00e8ve. Curitiba, 2000.</ref> In 2002, he completed a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] in State Law at the same institution with the thesis ''\"Constitutional Jurisdiction as Democracy\"'', guided by [[Mar\u00e7al Justen Filho]].<ref>Moro, S\u00e9rgio Fernando. [https://acervodigital.ufpr.br/bitstream/handle/1884/43165/Tese%20Moro.pdf?sequence=1 ''Jurisdi\u00e7\u00e3o constitucional como democracia'']. Thesis presented to the Postgraduate Course in Law of the Federal University of Paran\u00e1, as a partial requirement to obtain the title of Doctor, having as advisor Prof. Dr. Mar\u00e7al Justen Filho. Curitiba, 2002.</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://noticias.r7.com/brasil/rapido-discreto-e-obstinado-conheca-o-juiz-que-se-tornou-o-pesadelo-dos-acusados-na-lava-jato-14042015|title=R\u00e1pido, discreto e obstinado: conhe\u00e7a o juiz que se tornou o pesadelo dos acusados na Lava Jato|date=2015-04-14|work=R7.com|access-date=2018-11-19|language=pt-BR}}</ref> In 2007, he participated in the [[International Visitor Leadership Program]] in which he visited U.S. agencies and institutions responsible for preventing and combating money laundering.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://buscatextual.cnpq.br/buscatextual/visualizacv.do?id=K8747305D4#FormacaoAcademicaTitulacao|title=Curriculum vitae|last1=Moro|first1=Sergio|date=28 October 2013|website=Curr\u00edculo Lattes|publisher=CNPq|language=Portuguese|access-date=8 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 1996, Moro started teaching to law graduates at his ''[[alma mater]]'', the [[Federal University of Paran\u00e1]]. This very same year, he became a [[federal judge]] in [[Porto Alegre]], before moving to [[Joinville, Santa Catarina]], in 1999. Between 2003 and 2007, Moro worked in a case involving the public bank Banestado. The investigation resulted in the arrest of nearly 200 people for [[tax evasion]] and [[money laundering]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/pr/parana/noticia/2014/11/comissao-aprova-homenagens-sergio-moro-e-ao-papa-na-assembleia.html|title=Comiss\u00e3o aprova homenagens a S\u00e9rgio Moro e ao Papa na Assembleia|date=25 November 2014|publisher=G1|language=Portuguese|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, he worked with [[Rosa Weber]], a minister of the [[Supreme Federal Court|Brazilian Supreme Court]], in the [[Mensal\u00e3o scandal|''Mensal\u00e3o'' scandal]]. Weber called him because of his experience with cases involving financial crimes, more specifically money laundering.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/poder/51967-grupo-de-juizes-auxilia-stf-no-julgamento-do-mensalao.shtml|title=Grupo de ju\u00edzes auxilia STF no julgamento do mensal\u00e3o|publisher=Folha de S\u00e3o Paulo|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Operation Car Wash ===\n{{Main|Operation Car Wash}}\n[[File:S\u00e9rgio Moro (cropped).jpg|thumb|Moro in 2015.]]\nIn 2014, while working in [[Curitiba]], Sergio Moro became one of the head judges in [[Operation Car Wash]] ({{lang-pt|Opera\u00e7\u00e3o Lava Jato}}), a massive criminal investigation that started as a money laundering case and evolved to a huge corruption scandal crackdown, involving bribery and misappropriation of public funds by political authorities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ebc.com.br/noticias/politica/2016/03/saiba-porque-lava-jato-e-considerada-maior-investigacao-sobre-corrupcao-da|title=Saiba por que a Lava Jato \u00e9 considerada a maior investiga\u00e7\u00e3o da hist\u00f3ria do Brasil|publisher=|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> The investigation was modeled after [[Mani pulite]] in Italy.<ref name=\"mani\">{{cite web | url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2019/08/anti-corruption-crusades-paved-way-bolsonaro/596449/ | title=The Dirty Problems With Operation Car Wash | publisher=The Atlantic | date=21 August 2019 | accessdate=22 August 2019 | author=Bevins, Vincent}}</ref> Corruption scandals in Brazil usually take a long time to investigate and the whole legal process tends to drag. However, at an unusual speed, Moro authorized further investigations, detentions and questioning of suspects.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://politica.estadao.com.br/blogs/fausto-macedo/moro-sonha-com-fim-da-lava-jato-ate-dezembro/|title= Moro sonha com o fim da Lava Jato at\u00e9 dezembro|publisher=Estadao|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> By late 2017, at least 120 sentences were carried and 175 people were sent to jail. Despite some criticism from fellow jurists for being a \"media darling\", Moro enjoyed high popularity with the Brazilian people and became one of the main faces in the fight against corruption in the country, at least in the public eye.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/world-latin-america-35978337/who-is-sergio-moro-the-judge-making-brazil-s-headlines|title=Who is Sergio Moro, the judge making Brazil\u2019s headlines?|publisher=BBC|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nDespite the criticism of the speed with which he passed the sentences for such a huge case,<ref>{{cite web|url= http://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2016/10/04/estamos-em-tempos-excepcionais-diz-moro-ao-defender-prisoes-preventivas.htm|title='Estamos em tempos excepcionais', diz Moro ao defender pris\u00f5es preventivas|publisher=UOL|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> his actions received the backing of the Brazilian Supreme Court and most of his sentences and decisions were upheld in higher courts.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.em.com.br/app/noticia/politica/2016/10/04/interna_politica,810853/em-dois-anos-e-meio-apenas-tres-sentencas-da-lava-jato-chegaram-ao-fi.shtml|title=Em dois anos e meio, apenas tr\u00eas senten\u00e7as da Lava Jato chegaram ao final no TRF4|publisher=|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> By late 2016, Moro had sent 28 people to jail on charges of corruption, with four of them having their sentences reduced by a higher judge and four being set free upon further deliberation. Overall, in Operation Car Wash, 71% of the sentences given by Moro were upheld by the Brazilian [[Regional Federal Courts]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://politica.estadao.com.br/blogs/fausto-macedo/tribunal-ratifica-ou-sobe-pena-de-71-dos-condenados-por-moro/|title=Tribunal ratifica ou sobe pena de 71% dos condenados por Moro|publisher=O Estado de S.\u202fPaulo|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Moro sentenced former Brazilian president, [[Luiz In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva]], to 9 and a half years in jail, on the charges of money laundering and passive corruption. The sentencing caused an uproar in Brazil, with many widely supporting and saluting the judge for his decision, with others claiming he was getting ahead of himself.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/05/world/americas/brazil-lula-prison.html|title=Judge Orders Brazil\u2019s Ex-President \u2018Lula\u2019 to Begin Prison Term on Friday|publisher=The New York Times|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> Lula was considered the frontrunner for the 2018 presidential election.<ref name=\"mani\"/>\n\n=== Minister of Justice ===\nDuring his many encounters with media and further interviews, Sergio Moro always called himself \"apolitical\" and said he had no interested in joining the political world. However, right after the [[2018 Brazilian general election|2018 elections]], rumors started to circulate that the president-elect of Brazil, [[Jair Bolsonaro]], was considering nominating Moro to head the [[Ministry of Justice (Brazil)|Ministry of Justice]]. Despite claiming he was unaware of plans to make him justice minister before his invitation, it was later discovered that Moro was contacted by Paulo Guedes, an incoming member of Bolsonaro's administration, during Bolsonaro\u2019s election campaign.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Albuquerque |first1=Carlos |title=Controversial appointment |url=https://www.dandc.eu/en/article/brazils-newly-appointed-justice-minister-accused-political-interference |website= D+C, development and cooperation}}</ref> Exactly four days after the election, on 1 November 2018, Moro met with Bolsonaro in [[Rio de Janeiro]], and it was then announced that, in fact, he would become a minister in Bolsonaro's administration.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2018/11/01/moro-aceita-convite-de-bolsonaro-para-comandar-o-ministerio-da-justica.ghtml|title=Moro aceita convite de Bolsonaro para comandar o Minist\u00e9rio da Justi\u00e7a|publisher=G1|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-10-18/bolsonaro-embraces-aura-of-anti-graft-judge-in-campaign-push|title=This Man Is Playing a Big Role in Brazil\u2019s Election\u2014and He Isn\u2019t Even on the Ballot|publisher=Bloomberg.com|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nHis nomination was well received by fellow [[magistrate]]s across the country,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/brasil/associacao-dos-magistrados-elogia-a-escolha-de-moro-para-ministerio-01112018|title=Associa\u00e7\u00e3o dos Magistrados elogia a escolha de Moro para Minist\u00e9rio|publisher=R7|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref> but opponents of Bolsonaro and some of the press criticized the decision on the grounds of conflict of interest, claiming that Moro's sentencing of former president Lu\u00eds In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva greatly benefited Bolsonaro's bid for the presidency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/internacional/ultimas-noticias/2018/11/01/analise-por-que-a-nomeacao-de-moro-por-bolsonaro-caiu-mal-na-imprensa-internacional.htm|title=An\u00e1lise: Por que a nomea\u00e7\u00e3o de Moro por Bolsonaro caiu mal na imprensa internacional?|publisher=UOL|access-date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 May 2019, president Bolsonaro expressed the intention of nominating Moro to the Supreme Federal Court, replacing Justice [[Celso de Mello]], who will retire, at age 75, in 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2019/05/12/bolsonaro-diz-que-vai-indicar-sergio-moro-para-vaga-no-stf.ghtml|title=Bolsonaro diz que vai indicar S\u00e9rgio Moro para vaga no STF|publisher=G1|language=pt|first=Luiz Felipe|last=Babi\u00e9ri|date=12 May 2019|accessdate=13 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 April 2020, after an unjustified discharge of [[Federal Police of Brazil|Federal Police]]'s Director-General Maur\u00edcio Valeixo by president Bolsonaro, Moro announced he would leave the Ministry, while denouncing the president's intention to meddle in investigations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2020/04/sergio-moro-o-juiz-da-lava-jato-anuncia-sua-demissao-do-governo-bolsonaro.shtml|title=Sergio Moro, o juiz da Lava Jato, anuncia sua demiss\u00e3o do governo Bolsonaro|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|language=pt|first=Leandro|last=Colon|date=24 April 2020|accessdate=24 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\n[[File:Entrevistas Diversas (21094916379).jpg|thumb|right|Moro holding a press conference in September 2015]]\nMoro's methods have been questioned by his peers and audited by Brazilian Justices since 2005.<ref name=\"conjur.com.br\">{{cite web|url=http://www.conjur.com.br/2015-mai-05/excessos-sergio-moro-sao-discutidos-cnj-2005|title=Excessos de Sergio Moro s\u00e3o discutidos no STF e no CNJ pelo menos desde 2005|publisher=}}</ref> In 2007, when a defendant wasn't to be found at home, he issued an order to monitor the lists of passengers of all airliners flying from Ciudad del Este in Paraguay and from Porto Alegre in Brazil to Curitiba in order to track the movements of the defendant's attorneys.<ref name=\"conjur.com.br\"/> From 2007 through 2010, he issued an order to record and collect all phone communications and visitor booth talks between all inmates, their families and attorneys at Catanduvas Federal Penitentiary in order to \"prevent future crimes\".<ref name=\"conjur.com.br\"/>\n\nThese cases, among others, have been considered excesses and have brought grave criticism on Moro. Justice [[Celso de Mello]] has officially accused Moro of condoning a \"nosy police state\" and acting as an \"investigative judge\".<ref name=\"conjur.com.br\"/> Additionally, Brazilian Justice [[Gilmar Mendes]] said he was worried about Moro's actions. For him, the case showed a \"set of abusive acts\" and \"objectionable excesses\" practiced by the judge. In his dissenting opinion he wrote that they are \"unacceptable behaviors in which resistance or nonconformity of the magistrate is envisaged, when contradicted by decision of superior instance\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://politica.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,supremo-ja-analisou-excesso-de-moro-no-caso-banestado,10000023234|title=Supremo j\u00e1 analisou \u2018excesso\u2019 de Moro no caso Banestado - Pol\u00edtica - Estad\u00e3o|work=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=2018-11-19|language=pt-BR}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 December 2016, at a ceremony in which Moro was awarded a Man of the Year prize by Brazilian Editora Tr\u00eas publishing house, Moro was photographed laughing alongside Brazilian Senator [[A\u00e9cio Neves]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2016/12/07/viu-esta-foto-entenda-o-que-esta-por-tras-da-polemica-despertada-por-ela.htm|title=Viu esta foto? Entenda por que a descontra\u00e7\u00e3o entre Moro e A\u00e9cio repercutiu - Not\u00edcias - Pol\u00edtica|publisher=}}</ref> [[PSDB]]'s candidate in Brazil's [[2014 Brazilian general election|2014 Presidential Election]] and main critic of [[Workers' Party (Brazil)|PT]]'s tenures in office. Since PT is the party most scrutinized by Operation Carwash, the photograph has caused an uproar among PT supporters. During an interview, Moro has said that \"the photograph was unfortunate, but there's no bias in my decisions as a judge\", while also remarking that Neves is not under his jurisdiction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2016/12/1840125-moro-diz-que-foto-com-aecio-foi-infeliz-mas-nega-parcialidade.shtml|title=Moro diz que foto com A\u00e9cio foi 'infeliz', mas nega parcialidade|publisher=}}</ref>  Neves was accused by five witnesses at Operation Carwash<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/parlatorio/quem-nao-conhece-o-esquema-do-aecio-sergio-machado|title=\"Quem n\u00e3o conhece o esquema do A\u00e9cio?\", pergunta Sergio Machado|first=Jos\u00e9|last=Antonio|publisher=}}</ref> of taking R$300,000 in bribes from [[Alberto Youssef]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/parlatorio/aecio-neves-teria-recebido-r-300-mil-em-propina-da-utc-diz-delator|title=A\u00e9cio Neves teria recebido R$ 300 mil em propina da UTC, diz delator|first=|last=marcelop|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe speed with which Moro has treated specific actions that involve figures from the Brazilian left and his courteous relationship with members of the former opposition, some of which under investigation themselves, has been criticized by Brazilian jurists<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redebrasilatual.com.br/politica/2018/01/juristas-denunciam-lawfare-no-brasil-atraves-de-carta-internacional|title=Juristas denunciam 'lawfare' no Brasil atrav\u00e9s de carta internacional|publisher=}}</ref> and left-wing activists and politicians, who accuse Moro of being part of a [[lawfare]] strategy<ref>{{cite web|url=http://justificando.cartacapital.com.br/2018/04/10/a-ultraceleridade-seletiva-da-lava-jato-e-forma-de-lawfare/|title=A ultraceleridade seletiva da Lava Jato \u00e9 forma de Lawfare|date=10 April 2018|publisher=}}</ref> in order to ostracize PT and bring PSDB to power.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cartacampinas.com.br/2018/06/x-ocupado-com-pt-e-viagens-internacionais-moro-esta-sem-tempo-para-julgar-corrupcao-do-psdb/|title=Ocupado com PT e viagens internacionais, Moro est\u00e1 sem tempo para julgar corrup\u00e7\u00e3o do PSDB|date=12 June 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nDuring a lecture at Harvard University in 2017, S\u00e9rgio Moro stated that he considers the use of [[slush funds|undeclared donations]] \u2013 a crime in Brazilian electoral law \u2013 to fund elections more damaging than illicit enrichment through corruption: \"If I take this bribe and deposit the money in Switzerland, the money stays there, it isn\u2019t harming anyone at the moment. If, however, I use the money to fraud and win an election, I find that terrible.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://politica.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,caixa-2-e-pior-que-corrupcao-para-enriquecimento-ilicito,70001732141 |title=Caixa 2 \u00e9 pior que corrup\u00e7\u00e3o para enriquecimento il\u00edcito, diz S\u00e9rgio Moro |date=8 April 2017 |website=Estad\u00e3o |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.valor.com.br/politica/4931997/para-moro-caixa-dois-e-pior-que-enriquecimento-ilicito |title=Para Moro, caixa dois \u00e9 pior que enriquecimento il\u00edcito |date=8 April 2017 |website= Valor Econ\u00f4mico |access-date= 8 December 2018}}</ref> On May, 2017, then-congressman [[Onyx Lorenzoni]] admitted to having used slush funds donated by [[JBS S.A.|JBS]] in his 2014 campaign for Congress.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://congressoemfoco.uol.com.br/especial/noticias/em-video-deputado-onyx-lorenzoni-admite-ter-recebido-dinheiro-de-caixa-2/ |title=Onyx Lorenzoni admite ter recebido dinheiro de caixa dois da JBS |date=19 May 2017 |website=Congresso em Foco |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2018/10/braco-direito-de-bolsonaro-admitiu-ter-recebido-em-caixa-2-da-jbs.shtml |title=Bra\u00e7o direito de Bolsonaro admitiu ter recebido caixa 2 da JBS |date=15 October 2018 |website=Folha de S\u00e3o Paulo |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.valor.com.br/politica/5971261/moro-diz-admirar-colega-de-ministerio-que-recebeu-caixa-2-da-jbs |title=Moro diz \"admirar\" colega de minist\u00e9rio que recebeu caixa 2 da JBS |date=6 November 2018 |website=Valor Econ\u00f4mico |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref> Lorenzoni has been appointed [[Chief of Staff of Brazil|Chief of Staff]] by president-elect Jair Bolsonaro;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/eleicoes/2018/noticias/2018/10/30/quem-e-onyx-lorenzoni-ministro-da-casa-civil-do-governo-de-jair-bolsonaro.htm |title=Quem \u00e9 Onyx Lorenzoni, futuro ministro da Casa Civil no governo Bolsonaro |date=30 October 2018 |website=Folha de S\u00e3o Paulo |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref> upon being questioned by the press about Lorenzoni\u2019s public admission on the use of slush funds, Moro has stated that Lorenzoni has already apologized to him and has his \"personal trust\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/moro-lista-propostas-e-diz-que-perseguicao-politica-a-lula-e-alibi-falso/ |title=Em coletiva, Moro explica diverg\u00eancias com Bolsonaro e lista propostas |date=6 November 2018 |website=Exame |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noticias.r7.com/brasil/moro-defende-onyx-lorenzoni-e-diz-que-confia-em-seu-trabalho-04122018 |title=Moro defende Onyx Lorenzoni e diz que confia em seu trabalho |date=4 December 2018 |website=R7 |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2018/11/06/sergio-moro-ministro-governo-bolsonaro-pacote-anticorrupcao-membros-lava-jato.htm |title=Moro aponta Lava Jato e pacote anticorrup\u00e7\u00e3o como nortes e v\u00ea Bolsonaro \"ponderado\" |date=6 November 2018 |website=UOL |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://agenciabrasil.ebc.com.br/politica/noticia/2018-12/moro-reafirma-confianca-pessoal-em-onyx |title=Moro reafirma \"confian\u00e7a pessoal\" em Onyx |date=4 December 2018 |website=Ag\u00eancia Brasil |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://veja.abril.com.br/politica/moro-diz-ter-confianca-pessoal-em-onyx-que-admitiu-caixa-dois/ |title=Moro diz ter \"confian\u00e7a pessoal\" em Onyx, que admitiu caixa dois |date=4 December 2018 |website=Veja |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref> In November, 2018, Senator [[Roberto Requi\u00e3o]] proposed a bill called \"Lorenzoni Law\", which would grant immediate pardon for anyone found guilty of electoral and public administration crimes or crimes against the national financial system, as long as they ask for forgiveness. This proposal, although official, has been considered a joke on Moro\u2019s statements.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2018/11/requiao-ironiza-moro-e-propoe-projeto-de-lei-onyx-lorenzoni.shtml |title=Requi\u00e3o ironiza Moro e prop\u00f5e projeto de lei \"\u00d4nix Lorenzoni\" |date=8 November 2018 |website=Folha de S\u00e3o Paulo |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://politica.estadao.com.br/blogs/coluna-do-estadao/requiao-ironiza-moro-e-propoe-lei-onyx-para-perdoar-arrependidos/ |title=Requi\u00e3o ironiza Moro e prop\u00f5e \u2018Lei Onyx\u2019 para perdoar arrependidos |date=8 November 2018 |website=Estad\u00e3o |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/requiao-cria-projeto-lorenzoni-de-perdao-a-criminosos-arrependidos/ |title=Requi\u00e3o prop\u00f5e \"Lei Lorenzoni\" de perd\u00e3o para criminosos arrependidos |date=8 November 2018 |website=Exame |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Telegram leaks ===\n{{Vaza Jato |expanded=all}}\nOn 9 June 2019, the online newspaper ''[[The Intercept]]'' published leaked [[Telegram (app)|Telegram]] messages between Moro and the Operation Car Wash lead prosecutor [[Deltan Dallagnol]], in which Moro allegedly sent advice and instructions to the prosecutor in order to interfere in the investigation that ultimately led to the trial and imprisonment of former president Lula da Silva.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theintercept.com/2019/06/09/brazil-lula-operation-car-wash-sergio-moro/|title=Breach of Ethics: Exclusive: Leaked Chats Between Brazilian Judge and Prosecutor Who Imprisoned Lula Reveal Prohibited Collaboration and Doubts Over Evidence|last=Fishman|first=Andrew|last2=Martins|first2=Rafael Moro|date=2019-06-09|website=The Intercept|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-10|last3=Demori|first3=Leandro|last4=Santi|first4=Alexandre de|last5=Greenwald|first5=Glenn}}</ref> He was accused of not showing impartiality as a judge of da Silva's trial.<ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/25/world/americas/bolsonaro-brazil-phone-hack-corruption.html|title=Jair Bolsonaro, Brazil President, Says His Phones Were Hacked|author=Londo\u00f1o, Ernesto|date=25 July 2019|publisher=The New York Times|accessdate=1 August 2019}}</ref> Three days later, another conversation was leaked, revealing a secret meeting between Dallagnol and Supreme Court Justice [[Luiz Fux]], asking for his support against the then fellow Supreme Court judge [[Teori Zavascki]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/operacao-lava-jato/noticia/2019/06/12/em-nova-mensagem-divulgada-por-site-dallagnol-diz-que-fux-apoiou-moro-em-queda-de-braco-com-teori.ghtml|title=Em nova mensagem divulgada por site, Dallagnol diz que Fux apoiou Moro em 'queda de bra\u00e7o' com Teori|date=12 June 2019|publisher=G1|language=pt|trans-title=In New Message Published By Website, Dallagnol Says That Fux Supported Moro In 'Arm Wrestling' With Teori|accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref> Moro has thoroughly denied any wrongdoing during the course of Operation Carwash and claimed that the [[Vaza Jato|conversations leaked]] by ''The Intercept'' were misrepresented by the press.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/app/noticia/politica/2019/06/10/interna_politica,761721/nao-tem-orientacao-nenhuma-ali-diz-moro-antes-de-abandonar-coletiva.shtml|title=Moro nega ter orientado procuradores da Lava-Jato e abandona entrevista|date=2019-06-10|website=Correio Braziliense|language=pt-br|access-date=2019-07-01}}</ref> He also claimed that the messages could be inauthentic.<ref name=\"nytimes\" />\n\nOn June 12th, Brazilian news magazine ''[[Veja (magazine)|Veja]]'' published a report accusing Moro of \u201cillegally\u201d steering prosecutors as they worked to convict Brazilian politicians and \"overstepping his role as judge,\" claiming that its journalists had spent a fortnight pouring over nearly 650,000 leaked messages between officials involved in the investigation, and concluded the former judge was guilty of serious \u201cirregularities.\u201d Following the report, Moro released a statement condemning \u201cthe distorted and sensationalist diffusion of supposed messages obtained by criminal means.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://veja.abril.com.br/politica/dialogos-veja-capa-intercept-moro-dallagnol/|title=Novos di\u00e1logos revelam que Moro orientava ilegalmente a\u00e7\u00f5es da Lava Jato|website=VEJA.com|language=pt-BR|access-date=2019-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/jul/05/brazil-sergio-moro-jair-bolsonaro-justice-minister|title=Brazil: calls grow for Bolsonaro ally to quit after 'devastating' report on leaks|last=correspondent|first=Tom Phillips Latin America|date=2019-07-05|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-09-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Torquato Jardim]]<br />{{small|''as Minister of Justice''}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Ministry of Justice and Public Security (Brazil)|Minister of Justice and Public Security]]|rows=2|years=2019\u20132020}}\n{{s-vac|rows=2}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Raul Jungmann]]<br />{{small|''as Minister of Public Security''}}}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Bolsonaro cabinet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moro, Sergio}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Maring\u00e1]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Venetian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian judges]]\n[[Category:Brazilian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Ministers of Justice of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Federal University of Paran\u00e1 faculty]]\n", "name_user": "A.WagnerC", "label": "safe", "comment": "ref", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S%C3%A9rgio_Moro"}
{"title_page": "Stovepipe Wells, California", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|name          = Stovepipe Wells\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            =  \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        =[[Unincorporated area|Unincorporated community]]\n|image_skyline          = Stovepipe Wells, Death Valley National Park, CA (28222558218).jpg\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = General store and sign at Stovepipe Wells, December 2017\n|pushpin_map            =California#USA\n|pushpin_label_position =bottom\n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    =Location in California##Location within the United States\n<!-- Location ------------------>\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       ={{Flagu|United States}} \n|subdivision_type1      = State\n|subdivision_name1      = {{flag|California}}\n|subdivision_type2      =County\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Inyo County, California|Inyo County]]\n|subdivision_type3      =\n|subdivision_name3      = \n|<!-- Politics ----------------->\n|established_title      =  <!-- Settled -->\n|established_date       =\n|coordinates            = {{coord|36|36|22|N|117|08|47|W|region:US-CA|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    =  <ref name=gnis>{{gnis|235564}}</ref>\n|elevation_m            =3 \n|elevation_ft           =10\n|footnotes              = \n{{Designation list|embed=yes|designation1=California|designation1_number=826}}\n}}\n'''Stovepipe Wells''' is a small way-station in the northern part of [[Death Valley]], in [[Unincorporated area|unincorporated community]] [[Inyo County, California|Inyo County]], [[California]].\n\n==Geography and names==\nStovepipe Wells is located at {{coord|36|36|22|N|117|08|47|W}} and is US Geological Survey (USGS) feature ID 235564.<ref name=gnis /> It is entirely inside [[Death Valley National Park]] and along [[California State Route 190|State Route 190 (SR190)]] at less than {{convert|10|ft|m}} above [[sea level]].  West on SR190 is Towne Pass at about {{convert|4950|ft|m}} above sea level. Eventually, the road meets Panamint Valley Road at Panamint Junction in the [[Panamint Valley]]. East on SR190 the road leads to [[Furnace Creek, California|Furnace Creek]] and [[Death Valley Junction, California|Death Valley Junction]].\n\nVariant names listed for the [[Inyo County, California|Inyo County]] location by USGS include Stove Pipe Wells Hotel and Stovepipe Wells Hotel. The US Postal Service ZIP Code is 92328, and the locale name is spelled ''Stove Pipe Wells'' in some postal renditions. It is commonly referred to as Stovepipe Wells Village.\n\n===Climate===\nAccording to the [[K\u00f6ppen Climate Classification]] system, Stovepipe Wells has a [[Desert climate#Hot desert climates|hot desert climate]], abbreviated \"BWh\" on climate maps.<ref name=\"weatherbase.com\">[http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather-summary.php3?s=595104&cityname=Stovepipe+Wells%2C+California%2C+United+States+of+America&units= Climate Summary for Stovepipe Wells, California]</ref> Its average high temperature is greater than 100&nbsp;\u00b0F from June through September.<ref name=\"weatherbase.com\"/>\n\n{{Weather box\n|location = Stovepipe Wells, California\n|single line = Y\n|Jan high F = 63.9\n|Feb high F = 69.1\n|Mar high F = 78.5\n|Apr high F = 87.8\n|May high F = 97.9\n|Jun high F = 107.9\n|Jul high F = 114.1\n|Aug high F = 112.0\n|Sep high F = 102.8\n|Oct high F = 88.9\n|Nov high F = 72.5\n|Dec high F = 60.9\n|year high F =\n|Jan mean F = 52.9\n|Feb mean F = 58.6\n|Mar mean F = 67.8\n|Apr mean F = 76.0\n|May mean F = 86.0\n|Jun mean F = 95.1\n|Jul mean F = 101.6\n|Aug mean F = 99.4\n|Sep mean F = 90.6\n|Oct mean F = 77.0\n|Nov mean F = 61.9\n|Dec mean F = 50.7\n|year mean F =\n|Jan low F = 41.9\n|Feb low F = 48.0\n|Mar low F = 57.0\n|Apr low F = 64.1\n|May low F = 74.1\n|Jun low F = 82.3\n|Jul low F = 89.0\n|Aug low F = 86.7\n|Sep low F = 78.4\n|Oct low F = 65.0\n|Nov low F = 51.3\n|Dec low F = 40.5\n|year low F =\n|Jan precipitation inch = 0.4\n|Feb precipitation inch = 0.7\n|Mar precipitation inch = 0.7\n|Apr precipitation inch = 0.3\n|May precipitation inch = 0.2\n|Jun precipitation inch = 0.1\n|Jul precipitation inch = 0.2\n|Aug precipitation inch = 0.3\n|Sep precipitation inch = 0.2\n|Oct precipitation inch = 0.1\n|Nov precipitation inch = 0.4\n|Dec precipitation inch = 0.4\n|year precipitation inch = \n| precipitation colour    = green\n|source 1 = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather.php3?s=595104&cityname=Stovepipe-Wells-California-United-States-of-America&units=us |title=Monthly Averages for Stovepipe Wells, CA |publisher=weatherbase.com |date= |accessdate=2017-12-24}}</ref>\n|date=December 2017\n}}\n\n==History==\nThe first temporary settlement at Stovepipe Wells came into being when a road between Rhyolite and Skidoo was begun in 1906 to ameliorate the approach to the mine at Skidoo. A collection of tents was erected to serve travelers with food, drink and lodging.\n\nIn 1925, entrepreneur Bob Eichmann began construction of the hotel at Stovepipe Wells, along with a scenic toll road through Death Valley. This marked the beginning of the transition from mining community to tourist destination.\n\nThe settlement is now registered as [[California Historical Landmark]] #826.<ref name=CHL>{{cite ohp|826|Stovepipe Wells|2012-10-07}}</ref>\n\n==Facilities==\nStovepipe Wells Village is home to the [http://deathvalleyhotels.com Stovepipe Wells Hotel], a full-service hotel with swimming pool. The General Store offers sundries and food, and is adjacent to a gas station. Stovepipe Wells Village also houses the Badwater Saloon and Toll Road restaurant, The Nugget Gift Shop and a ranger station.\n\nThe default format for wired telephone numbers in the community is in the [[Telephone exchange|Death Valley exchange]]: (760) 786-xxxx. The community had manual telephone service until the late 1980s.\n\nThe community is contained within the Great Basin Unified Air Pollution Control District.\n\n==Nearby features==\n* Close to town are some fairly large and accessible stationary sand dunes on the floor of Death Valley. The dunes are roughly {{convert|7|mi|km}} long in the east\u2013west axis. They are located in the space between Salt Creek and Emigrant Wash.\n* ''Stovepipe Well'', for which the community is named, is shown to the northeast at {{coord|36|39|33|N|117|04|44|W}}.\n* ''Stovepipe Wells Airport'' is to the southwest at {{coord|36|36|14|N|117|09|33|W}}. The airport has an identifier of L09 and features a {{convert|3250|ft|m|adj=on}} paved runway.\n\n----\n\n<gallery>\nImage:Stovepipe_Wells_downtown.jpg|Stovepipe Wells \"downtown\"\nImage:Stovepipe_Wells_FD_truck.jpg|Stovepipe Wells Fire Dept truck\nImage:Stovepipe_Wells_Burned_Wagons.jpg|Burned Wagons plaque\nImage:Stovepipe_Wells_saloon.jpg|Stovepipe Wells saloon at dusk\nImage:Stovepipe_Wells_store.jpg|Stovepipe Wells general store at dusk\nImage:Old stovepipe wells 01.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n==Sources==\n{{reflist}}\n* ''7350.7U Location Identifiers'', The National Flight Data Center, Federal Aviation Administration ATPUBS, US Department of Transportation, September 1, 2005.\n* Map: Stovepipe Wells, California 7.5-minute quadrangle, US Geological Survey, 1988.\n* National Geographic Names Database, US Geological Survey, 1995.\n* California Air Resources Board web site.\n* Richard E. Lingenfelter. (1988) Death Valley and the Amargosa: A Land of Illusion: University of California Press. p.&nbsp;290, p.&nbsp;475.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [http://www.deathvalleyhotels.com Stovepipe Wells Village web site]\n* [http://www.nps.gov/deva National Park Service: Official Death Valley National Park website]\n\n{{Death Valley}}\n{{Inyo County, California}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Death Valley]]<!---for geography ?-